139,"position":2303,"tag_list":2304,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2310,"first_published_at":2311,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2312,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"From Manual to Autonomous: The Evolution of the Yard Management System","2025-11-09T08:51:36.812Z","2026-03-27T17:29:43.707Z","2026-03-27T17:29:43.731Z",110545702177019,"cf392b96-215d-4520-98df-98b0c524b818",{"_uid":1222,"body":1223,"link":2259,"title":1215,"author":2260,"excerpt":2286,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2288,"seo_image":2289,"seo_title":2291,"button_text":132,"cover_image":2292,"gated_asset":2296,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":2297,"background_color":2298,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"a46c9b98-cd98-47f0-a0a0-959083389e6f",{"type":66,"content":1224},[1225,1245,1264,1272,1281,1291,1310,1329,1343,1395,1404,1412,1426,1445,1454,1468,1482,1490,1540,1548,1557,1575,1577,1591,1610,1619,1649,1658,1667,1681,1690,1704,1713,1721,1730,1738,1747,1766,1775,1793,1858,1867,1875,1927,1935,1944,1973,1987,1995,2003,2012,2020,2029,2037,2059,2067,2076,2097,2106,2114,2123,2131,2163,2172,2180,2212,2221,2229,2251],{"type":112,"attrs":1226,"content":1227},{"textAlign":139},[1228,1234,1240],{"text":1229,"type":75,"marks":1230},"The ",[1231],{"type":149,"attrs":1232},{"color":1233},"#000000",{"text":1235,"type":75,"marks":1236},"evolution of yard management systems",[1237,1239],{"type":149,"attrs":1238},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1241,"type":75,"marks":1242}," is one of the most significant changes in logistics technology. In the past, traditional yard operations relied heavily on clipboards, paper logs, and manual tracking. This process was prone to human error, had limited visibility, and often faced operational bottlenecks. You may have experienced the frustration of misplaced trailers, delayed shipments, and hours wasted searching for assets in large facilities.",[1243],{"type":149,"attrs":1244},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1246,"content":1247},{"textAlign":139},[1248,1253,1259],{"text":1249,"type":75,"marks":1250},"Yard management plays a crucial role in your supply chain, bridging the gap between transportation and warehousing. When yard operations are inefficient, it affects various aspects such as dock scheduling and customer satisfaction. The stakes are high—",[1251],{"type":149,"attrs":1252},{"color":1233},{"text":1254,"type":75,"marks":1255},"autonomous yard management",[1256,1258],{"type":149,"attrs":1257},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1260,"type":75,"marks":1261}," goes beyond simply replacing manual processes with technology. It involves rethinking how goods move through your facilities.",[1262],{"type":149,"attrs":1263},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1265,"content":1266},{"textAlign":139},[1267],{"text":1268,"type":75,"marks":1269},"The transition from manual tracking to fully autonomous systems tackles the growing challenges of modern logistics: driver shortages, increasing demands for throughput, and the necessity for real-time visibility. This transformation is important today because your competitors are already using these technologies to gain operational advantages that you cannot afford to overlook.",[1270],{"type":149,"attrs":1271},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1273,"content":1274},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1275],{"text":1276,"type":75,"marks":1277},"The Journey from Manual to Autonomous Yard Management: A Brief History",[1278,1280],{"type":149,"attrs":1279},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":1282,"content":1284},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},3,[1285],{"text":1286,"type":75,"marks":1287},"The Era of Manual Yard Management",[1288,1290],{"type":149,"attrs":1289},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1292,"content":1293},{"textAlign":139},[1294,1299,1305],{"text":1295,"type":75,"marks":1296},"In the 1980s and early 1990s, logistics yards were filled with clipboards. ",[1297],{"type":149,"attrs":1298},{"color":1233},{"text":1300,"type":75,"marks":1301},"Paper-based logistics",[1302,1304],{"type":149,"attrs":1303},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1306,"type":75,"marks":1307}," were the norm, with yard managers using handwritten logs to keep track of trailer locations, driver check-ins, and equipment movements. Every transaction needed manual documentation, making the system prone to human error at every stage.",[1308],{"type":149,"attrs":1309},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1311,"content":1312},{"textAlign":139},[1313,1318,1324],{"text":1314,"type":75,"marks":1315},"The limitations were significant. If a form got misplaced, it could take hours to find a trailer. Operations faced delays as workers had to physically walk around the yard to find assets. ",[1316],{"type":149,"attrs":1317},{"color":1233},{"text":1319,"type":75,"marks":1320},"Human labor in yards",[1321,1323],{"type":149,"attrs":1322},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1325,"type":75,"marks":1326}," had its limits—you couldn't keep increasing the number of workers indefinitely, and even the most hardworking employees found it difficult to be accurate when managing hundreds of assets in large facilities.",[1327],{"type":149,"attrs":1328},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1330,"content":1331},{"textAlign":139},[1332,1338],{"text":1333,"type":75,"marks":1334},"Manual yard management",[1335,1337],{"type":149,"attrs":1336},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1339,"type":75,"marks":1340}," had three major problems:",[1341],{"type":149,"attrs":1342},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":1345},"bullet_list",[1346,1363,1379],{"type":1347,"content":1348},"list_item",[1349],{"type":112,"attrs":1350,"content":1351},{"textAlign":139},[1352,1358],{"text":1353,"type":75,"marks":1354},"Limited visibility",[1355,1357],{"type":149,"attrs":1356},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1359,"type":75,"marks":1360},": No real-time view of yard status or asset locations",[1361],{"type":149,"attrs":1362},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1364},[1365],{"type":112,"attrs":1366,"content":1367},{"textAlign":139},[1368,1374],{"text":1369,"type":75,"marks":1370},"Frequent errors",[1371,1373],{"type":149,"attrs":1372},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1375,"type":75,"marks":1376},": Handwritten logs led to misplaced trailers and incorrect inventory counts",[1377],{"type":149,"attrs":1378},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1380},[1381],{"type":112,"attrs":1382,"content":1383},{"textAlign":139},[1384,1390],{"text":1385,"type":75,"marks":1386},"Operational bottlenecks",[1387,1389],{"type":149,"attrs":1388},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1391,"type":75,"marks":1392},": Every gate transaction required multiple manual steps, creating throughput constraints",[1393],{"type":149,"attrs":1394},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1396,"content":1397},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1398],{"text":1399,"type":75,"marks":1400},"The Start of Digital Transformation",[1401,1403],{"type":149,"attrs":1402},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1405,"content":1406},{"textAlign":139},[1407],{"text":1408,"type":75,"marks":1409},"The introduction of mechanical handling equipment marked the first shift toward efficiency. Forklifts and yard trucks reduced physical strain, but the real change came when basic computer systems started being used in the yard.",[1410],{"type":149,"attrs":1411},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1413,"content":1414},{"textAlign":139},[1415,1421],{"text":1416,"type":75,"marks":1417},"Automated yard systems",[1418,1420],{"type":149,"attrs":1419},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1422,"type":75,"marks":1423}," emerged as Automated Storage and Retrieval Systems (AS/RS) optimized goods placement using programmed logic. These systems brought precision to warehouse operations, eliminating guesswork in inventory management.",[1424],{"type":149,"attrs":1425},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1427,"content":1428},{"textAlign":139},[1429,1434,1440],{"text":1430,"type":75,"marks":1431},"The integration with ",[1432],{"type":149,"attrs":1433},{"color":1233},{"text":1435,"type":75,"marks":1436},"Warehouse Management Systems (WMS)",[1437,1439],{"type":149,"attrs":1438},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1441,"type":75,"marks":1442}," created the foundation for modern yard operations. Digital oversight replaced paper trails, and operational accuracy improved dramatically as data flowed between systems rather than through manual entry.",[1443],{"type":149,"attrs":1444},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1446,"content":1447},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1448],{"text":1449,"type":75,"marks":1450},"Transforming Yard Operations with Robotics and Autonomous Vehicles",[1451,1453],{"type":149,"attrs":1452},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1455,"content":1456},{"textAlign":139},[1457,1463],{"text":1458,"type":75,"marks":1459},"Robotics in logistics ",[1460,1462],{"type":149,"attrs":1461},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1464,"type":75,"marks":1465},"has changed yard operations from being heavily reliant on manual labor to becoming more precise and efficient. Nowadays, yards use specialized robots for tasks like picking, packing, and sorting—jobs that used to require multiple workers. These machines excel at repetitive tasks, working tirelessly and accurately to process hundreds of items every hour without the risk of mistakes that often occur in manual work.",[1466],{"type":149,"attrs":1467},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1469,"content":1470},{"textAlign":139},[1471,1477],{"text":1472,"type":75,"marks":1473},"Autonomous vehicles yard ",[1474,1476],{"type":149,"attrs":1475},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1478,"type":75,"marks":1479},"solutions have brought about a new way of moving materials. Automated guided vehicles (AGVs) follow specific paths using sensors and magnetic strips to transport trailers and containers between different areas of the yard, such as staging zones and dock doors. These vehicles operate around the clock, eliminating the need for shift changes and breaks that can disrupt traditional workflows. In some facilities, aerial drones are also used for inventory scanning across large yards, quickly capturing the locations of assets in a matter of minutes instead of hours.",[1480],{"type":149,"attrs":1481},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1483,"content":1484},{"textAlign":139},[1485],{"text":1486,"type":75,"marks":1487},"The impact on key operational metrics is both measurable and significant:",[1488],{"type":149,"attrs":1489},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":1491},[1492,1508,1524],{"type":1347,"content":1493},[1494],{"type":112,"attrs":1495,"content":1496},{"textAlign":139},[1497,1503],{"text":1498,"type":75,"marks":1499},"Productivity gains",[1500,1502],{"type":149,"attrs":1501},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1504,"type":75,"marks":1505}," of 40-60% through continuous operation cycles",[1506],{"type":149,"attrs":1507},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1509},[1510],{"type":112,"attrs":1511,"content":1512},{"textAlign":139},[1513,1519],{"text":1514,"type":75,"marks":1515},"Order accuracy",[1516,1518],{"type":149,"attrs":1517},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1520,"type":75,"marks":1521}," improvements reaching 99%+ through automated verification",[1522],{"type":149,"attrs":1523},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1525},[1526],{"type":112,"attrs":1527,"content":1528},{"textAlign":139},[1529,1535],{"text":1530,"type":75,"marks":1531},"Fulfillment speed",[1532,1534],{"type":149,"attrs":1533},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1536,"type":75,"marks":1537}," increases of 30-50% from reduced handling times",[1538],{"type":149,"attrs":1539},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1541,"content":1542},{"textAlign":139},[1543],{"text":1544,"type":75,"marks":1545},"Robotics and autonomous vehicles work together as part of coordinated systems rather than functioning independently. AGVs communicate with warehouse management platforms to receive real-time instructions on which trailers need to be moved. Robotic sorters integrate with inventory systems to direct items to their designated staging areas. This seamless coordination creates an operation where machines handle physical tasks while software controls the logic behind each movement.",[1546],{"type":149,"attrs":1547},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1549,"content":1550},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1551],{"text":1552,"type":75,"marks":1553},"AI-Powered Innovations in Yard Management Systems",[1554,1556],{"type":149,"attrs":1555},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1558,"content":1559},{"textAlign":139},[1560,1564,1570],{"text":1229,"type":75,"marks":1561},[1562],{"type":149,"attrs":1563},{"color":1233},{"text":1565,"type":75,"marks":1566},"AI yard management system",[1567,1569],{"type":149,"attrs":1568},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1571,"type":75,"marks":1572}," is a significant advancement over robotic automation. It introduces intelligence that learns, adapts, and optimizes yard operations in real-time. This technology doesn't just perform tasks; it anticipates needs.",[1573],{"type":149,"attrs":1574},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1576},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},{"type":112,"attrs":1578,"content":1579},{"textAlign":139},[1580,1586],{"text":1581,"type":75,"marks":1582},"Predictive analytics logistics ",[1583,1585],{"type":149,"attrs":1584},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1587,"type":75,"marks":1588},"capabilities change the way you predict demand and allocate resources. AI algorithms examine historical data, seasonal changes, and external factors such as weather or market conditions to forecast trailer volumes weeks ahead of time. This allows you to strategically position assets before demand increases, eliminating the need for reactive management. Resource allocation becomes precise—you'll know exactly how many yard drivers, dock doors, and parking zones you'll require at any given moment.",[1589],{"type":149,"attrs":1590},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1592,"content":1593},{"textAlign":139},[1594,1599,1605],{"text":1595,"type":75,"marks":1596},"Computer vision applications bring unmatched precision to yard operations. Terminal's proprietary technology achieves ",[1597],{"type":149,"attrs":1598},{"color":1233},{"text":1600,"type":75,"marks":1601},"99.5% data accuracy",[1602,1604],{"type":149,"attrs":1603},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1606,"type":75,"marks":1607}," in identifying assets by automatically detecting container numbers, license plates, and equipment types without any human involvement. During check-in processes, the system identifies damage, flags quality control issues, and keeps visual records for dispute resolution—capturing information that manual inspections often overlook.",[1608],{"type":149,"attrs":1609},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1611,"content":1612},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1613],{"text":1614,"type":75,"marks":1615},"Autonomous Navigation for Efficient Movement",[1616,1618],{"type":149,"attrs":1617},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1620,"content":1621},{"textAlign":139},[1622,1627,1633,1638,1644],{"text":1623,"type":75,"marks":1624},"AI-powered autonomous navigation algorithms enhance movement patterns within your yard. These systems determine the most efficient routes for repositioning assets, consider congestion points, and adjust paths dynamically based on real-time conditions. Terminal's ",[1625],{"type":149,"attrs":1626},{"color":1233},{"text":1628,"type":75,"marks":1629},"SmartYard™",[1630,1632],{"type":149,"attrs":1631},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1634,"type":75,"marks":1635}," workflows utilize these AI capabilities to achieve ",[1636],{"type":149,"attrs":1637},{"color":1233},{"text":1639,"type":75,"marks":1640},"50%+ throughput improvements",[1641,1643],{"type":149,"attrs":1642},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1645,"type":75,"marks":1646},", transforming chaotic yard movements into orchestrated precision. With this technology, yard management evolves from reactive problem-solving to proactive optimization.",[1647],{"type":149,"attrs":1648},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1650,"content":1651},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1652],{"text":1653,"type":75,"marks":1654},"How IoT and Cloud Connectivity Are Changing Yard Operations",[1655,1657],{"type":149,"attrs":1656},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":1659,"content":1660},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1661],{"text":1662,"type":75,"marks":1663},"The Impact of IoT on Logistics Yards",[1664,1666],{"type":149,"attrs":1665},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1668,"content":1669},{"textAlign":139},[1670,1676],{"text":1671,"type":75,"marks":1672},"IoT in logistics yards ",[1673,1675],{"type":149,"attrs":1674},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1677,"type":75,"marks":1678},"has fundamentally changed how operators track and manage their assets. Sensors embedded throughout the yard environment continuously capture data from vehicles, trailers, and equipment, creating a real-time digital representation of physical operations. You can monitor trailer temperatures for refrigerated loads, track tire pressure on yard trucks, and receive instant alerts when equipment moves outside designated zones.",[1679],{"type":149,"attrs":1680},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1682,"content":1683},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1684],{"text":1685,"type":75,"marks":1686},"The Role of Cloud-Based Yard Management Software",[1687,1689],{"type":149,"attrs":1688},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1691,"content":1692},{"textAlign":139},[1693,1699],{"text":1694,"type":75,"marks":1695},"Cloud-based yard management software ",[1696,1698],{"type":149,"attrs":1697},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1700,"type":75,"marks":1701},"serves as the central nervous system connecting these distributed sensors and devices. The architecture eliminates the need for on-premise servers and enables instant data synchronization across your entire operation. When a trailer enters your facility in California, your team in New Jersey sees the same information simultaneously without delay or manual data entry.",[1702],{"type":149,"attrs":1703},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1705,"content":1706},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1707],{"text":1708,"type":75,"marks":1709},"Benefits of Scalability with Cloud-Native Platforms",[1710,1712],{"type":149,"attrs":1711},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1714,"content":1715},{"textAlign":139},[1716],{"text":1717,"type":75,"marks":1718},"The scalability advantage becomes apparent when you operate multiple facilities. A cloud-native platform like Terminal's Yard Operating System™ delivers single-pane-of-glass visibility across your entire yard network. You can compare performance metrics between sites, identify bottlenecks in real-time, and deploy successful workflows from one location to another with minimal configuration.",[1719],{"type":149,"attrs":1720},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1722,"content":1723},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1724],{"text":1725,"type":75,"marks":1726},"Breaking Down Data Silos with Connected Systems",[1727,1729],{"type":149,"attrs":1728},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1731,"content":1732},{"textAlign":139},[1733],{"text":1734,"type":75,"marks":1735},"Connected systems eliminate data silos that plague traditional yard operations. Your gate cameras communicate with inventory management modules, which trigger automated move tasks for yard drivers. This seamless device-to-device communication happens without human intervention, creating a responsive ecosystem that adapts to changing conditions throughout your operational day.",[1736],{"type":149,"attrs":1737},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1739,"content":1740},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1741],{"text":1742,"type":75,"marks":1743},"Terminal YOS: Leading the Charge Towards Fully Autonomous Yard Solutions",[1744,1746],{"type":149,"attrs":1745},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1748,"content":1749},{"textAlign":139},[1750,1755,1761],{"text":1751,"type":75,"marks":1752},"Terminal is leading the way in transforming yard logistics with a clear mission: to completely digitize and automate yard operations. The company's ",[1753],{"type":149,"attrs":1754},{"color":1233},{"text":1756,"type":75,"marks":1757},"AI-native Yard Operating System™ (YOS)",[1758,1760],{"type":149,"attrs":1759},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1762,"type":75,"marks":1763}," represents a fundamental shift from traditional yard management approaches, combining computer vision, real-time data infrastructure, and modular software applications into a single scalable system designed specifically for mid-market and large enterprise operators managing five or more warehouses.",[1764],{"type":149,"attrs":1765},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1767,"content":1768},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1769],{"text":1770,"type":75,"marks":1771},"Breakthrough Capabilities of Terminal YOS",[1772,1774],{"type":149,"attrs":1773},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1776,"content":1777},{"textAlign":139},[1778,1782,1788],{"text":1229,"type":75,"marks":1779},[1780],{"type":149,"attrs":1781},{"color":1233},{"text":1783,"type":75,"marks":1784},"Terminal YOS",[1785,1787],{"type":149,"attrs":1786},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1789,"type":75,"marks":1790}," stands out with its several groundbreaking features:",[1791],{"type":149,"attrs":1792},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":1794},[1795,1811,1826,1842],{"type":1347,"content":1796},[1797],{"type":112,"attrs":1798,"content":1799},{"textAlign":139},[1800,1806],{"text":1801,"type":75,"marks":1802},"Proprietary computer vision technology",[1803,1805],{"type":149,"attrs":1804},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1807,"type":75,"marks":1808}," achieving 99.5% data accuracy, eliminating the manual scanning and GPS tracking that plague conventional systems",[1809],{"type":149,"attrs":1810},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1812},[1813],{"type":112,"attrs":1814,"content":1815},{"textAlign":139},[1816,1821],{"text":171,"type":75,"marks":1817},[1818,1820],{"type":149,"attrs":1819},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1822,"type":75,"marks":1823}," with AI-powered workflows that automate gate processes from check-in to departure, delivering throughput improvements exceeding 50%",[1824],{"type":149,"attrs":1825},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1827},[1828],{"type":112,"attrs":1829,"content":1830},{"textAlign":139},[1831,1837],{"text":1832,"type":75,"marks":1833},"Terminal-in-a-Camera™",[1834,1836],{"type":149,"attrs":1835},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1838,"type":75,"marks":1839}," hardware kit enabling deployment in hours without trenching or extensive infrastructure modifications",[1840],{"type":149,"attrs":1841},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1843},[1844],{"type":112,"attrs":1845,"content":1846},{"textAlign":139},[1847,1853],{"text":1848,"type":75,"marks":1849},"Rapid ROI",[1850,1852],{"type":149,"attrs":1851},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1854,"type":75,"marks":1855}," typically achieved in under five months, addressing the financial concerns that often delay automation initiatives",[1856],{"type":149,"attrs":1857},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1859,"content":1860},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[1861],{"text":1862,"type":75,"marks":1863},"Key Benefits of Terminal YOS",[1864,1866],{"type":149,"attrs":1865},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1868,"content":1869},{"textAlign":139},[1870],{"text":1871,"type":75,"marks":1872},"With the Terminal YOS, you can expect the following key benefits:",[1873],{"type":149,"attrs":1874},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":1876},[1877,1887,1897,1907,1917],{"type":1347,"content":1878},[1879],{"type":112,"attrs":1880,"content":1881},{"textAlign":139},[1882],{"text":1883,"type":75,"marks":1884},"Scalable operations across your entire yard network",[1885],{"type":149,"attrs":1886},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1888},[1889],{"type":112,"attrs":1890,"content":1891},{"textAlign":139},[1892],{"text":1893,"type":75,"marks":1894},"Unified visibility into your yard activities",[1895],{"type":149,"attrs":1896},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1898},[1899],{"type":112,"attrs":1900,"content":1901},{"textAlign":139},[1902],{"text":1903,"type":75,"marks":1904},"Real-time asset tracking through live camera-driven yard maps",[1905],{"type":149,"attrs":1906},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1908},[1909],{"type":112,"attrs":1910,"content":1911},{"textAlign":139},[1912],{"text":1913,"type":75,"marks":1914},"Automated shipment planning that aligns inventory with upcoming moves",[1915],{"type":149,"attrs":1916},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":1918},[1919],{"type":112,"attrs":1920,"content":1921},{"textAlign":139},[1922],{"text":1923,"type":75,"marks":1924},"Configurable event-driven workflows that adapt to your specific operational requirements",[1925],{"type":149,"attrs":1926},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1928,"content":1929},{"textAlign":139},[1930],{"text":1931,"type":75,"marks":1932},"The cloud-native architecture of the system ensures that you can easily scale your operations while maintaining complete control over your processes. Say goodbye to rigid and static standard operating procedures (SOPs) that limit your flexibility - with Terminal YOS, you have the power to customize your workflows according to your unique needs.",[1933],{"type":149,"attrs":1934},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":1936,"content":1937},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[1938],{"text":1939,"type":75,"marks":1940},"Realizing the Benefits: Operational Efficiency, Cost Reduction, Safety Enhancements, And More Through Autonomous Yard Management",[1941,1943],{"type":149,"attrs":1942},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":1945,"content":1946},{"textAlign":139},[1947,1952,1957,1962,1968],{"text":1948,"type":75,"marks":1949},"The transformation ",[1950],{"type":149,"attrs":1951},{"color":1233},{"text":1215,"type":75,"marks":1953},[1954,1956],{"type":149,"attrs":1955},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1958,"type":75,"marks":1959}," delivers measurable improvements across every dimension of yard operations. You'll see ",[1960],{"type":149,"attrs":1961},{"color":1233},{"text":1963,"type":75,"marks":1964},"operational efficiency yard automation",[1965,1967],{"type":149,"attrs":1966},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1969,"type":75,"marks":1970}," manifest in dramatically reduced gate processing times—Terminal's Gate Acceleration™ application cuts transaction time by over 85%, while SmartYard™ workflows generate throughput improvements exceeding 50%. These aren't incremental gains; they represent fundamental shifts in how quickly you move assets through your facility.",[1971],{"type":149,"attrs":1972},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1974,"content":1975},{"textAlign":139},[1976,1982],{"text":1977,"type":75,"marks":1978},"Cost reduction logistics",[1979,1981],{"type":149,"attrs":1980},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":1983,"type":75,"marks":1984}," becomes tangible when you eliminate manual data entry, reduce labor costs by up to 75% at gate operations, and achieve ROI in under five months. Terminal's computer vision technology delivers 99.5% data accuracy without requiring manual scans or GPS devices, removing the ongoing expense of hardware maintenance and replacement.",[1985],{"type":149,"attrs":1986},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1988,"content":1989},{"textAlign":139},[1990],{"text":1991,"type":75,"marks":1992},"Safety improvements emerge naturally when you minimize human exposure to hazardous yard activities. Automated gate processes reduce the need for personnel to work in high-traffic areas, while AI-powered asset tracking eliminates the dangerous practice of workers navigating active yards to locate trailers. Terminal's Asset Movement application orchestrates yard moves systematically, reducing the risk of accidents caused by poor visibility or miscommunication.",[1993],{"type":149,"attrs":1994},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":1996,"content":1997},{"textAlign":139},[1998],{"text":1999,"type":75,"marks":2000},"The 90% reduction in asset search time and 12% decrease in driver detention fees demonstrate how autonomous systems create compounding benefits across your operation.",[2001],{"type":149,"attrs":2002},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2004,"content":2005},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2006],{"text":2007,"type":75,"marks":2008},"Overcoming Challenges on the Road to Full Autonomy: Adapting the Workforce and Tackling System Integration Issues in Autonomous Yards",[2009,2011],{"type":149,"attrs":2010},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2013,"content":2014},{"textAlign":139},[2015],{"text":2016,"type":75,"marks":2017},"Shifting to autonomous yard management requires a significant investment of capital. You'll need to spend a lot on computer vision systems, IoT sensors, robotics, and cloud infrastructure. These challenges in autonomous yards can put a strain on budgets, especially for mid-market operators who are trying to balance ROI timelines with immediate operational pressures.",[2018],{"type":149,"attrs":2019},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2021,"content":2022},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[2023],{"text":2024,"type":75,"marks":2025},"1. The Need for Workforce Adaptation",[2026,2028],{"type":149,"attrs":2027},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2030,"content":2031},{"textAlign":139},[2032],{"text":2033,"type":75,"marks":2034},"Another major obstacle is the need for logistics technology workforce adaptation. Your current team will require extensive retraining in order to work effectively alongside automated systems. This includes:",[2035],{"type":149,"attrs":2036},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":2038},[2039,2049],{"type":1347,"content":2040},[2041],{"type":112,"attrs":2042,"content":2043},{"textAlign":139},[2044],{"text":2045,"type":75,"marks":2046},"Gate clerks moving away from manual data entry and instead monitoring AI-powered workflows.",[2047],{"type":149,"attrs":2048},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2050},[2051],{"type":112,"attrs":2052,"content":2053},{"textAlign":139},[2054],{"text":2055,"type":75,"marks":2056},"Yard drivers transitioning from reactive task execution to managing orchestrated move sequences using mobile interfaces.",[2057],{"type":149,"attrs":2058},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2060,"content":2061},{"textAlign":139},[2062],{"text":2063,"type":75,"marks":2064},"It's important to note that this learning process may temporarily slow down operations during the implementation stages.",[2065],{"type":149,"attrs":2066},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2068,"content":2069},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[2070],{"text":2071,"type":75,"marks":2072},"2. The Complexity of System Integration",[2073,2075],{"type":149,"attrs":2074},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2077,"content":2078},{"textAlign":139},[2079,2084,2092],{"text":2080,"type":75,"marks":2081},"The difficulties of system integration",[2082],{"type":149,"attrs":2083},{"color":1233},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":2085},[2086,2090],{"type":2087,"attrs":2088},"link",{"href":2089,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://wisconsindot.gov/documents2/research/0092-24-14-final-report.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":2091},{"color":1233},{"text":2093,"type":75,"marks":2094},"make these challenges even more complicated. In order for your new Yard Operating System to work smoothly with your existing WMS, TMS, and ERP platforms, you need to establish seamless connectivity between them. However, legacy systems often lack modern APIs, which means you'll have to develop custom middleware solutions. Additionally, careful mapping will be necessary to ensure data synchronization across platforms and avoid any disruptions in operations.",[2095],{"type":149,"attrs":2096},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2098,"content":2099},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[2100],{"text":2101,"type":75,"marks":2102},"3. Addressing Employee Concerns",[2103,2105],{"type":149,"attrs":2104},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2107,"content":2108},{"textAlign":139},[2109],{"text":2110,"type":75,"marks":2111},"The human aspect is still crucial in this process. It's essential for you to address any worries your employees may have about job loss due to automation. At the same time, you must also demonstrate how automation can enhance their roles by shifting them away from repetitive tasks and towards strategic oversight and exception handling responsibilities.",[2112],{"type":149,"attrs":2113},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2115,"content":2116},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2117],{"text":2118,"type":75,"marks":2119},"Looking Ahead: The Future Of Yard Management Systems",[2120,2122],{"type":149,"attrs":2121},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2124,"content":2125},{"textAlign":139},[2126],{"text":2127,"type":75,"marks":2128},"The shift from manual to automated yard operations is happening quickly as new trends in yard management are changing the logistics industry. We're seeing AI move beyond simple automation to become advanced decision-making systems that can:",[2129],{"type":149,"attrs":2130},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":2132},[2133,2143,2153],{"type":1347,"content":2134},[2135],{"type":112,"attrs":2136,"content":2137},{"textAlign":139},[2138],{"text":2139,"type":75,"marks":2140},"Predict problems before they happen",[2141],{"type":149,"attrs":2142},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2144},[2145],{"type":112,"attrs":2146,"content":2147},{"textAlign":139},[2148],{"text":2149,"type":75,"marks":2150},"Reallocate resources based on real-time demand patterns",[2151],{"type":149,"attrs":2152},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2154},[2155],{"type":112,"attrs":2156,"content":2157},{"textAlign":139},[2158],{"text":2159,"type":75,"marks":2160},"Optimize yard layouts through continuous learning algorithms",[2161],{"type":149,"attrs":2162},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2164,"content":2165},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[2166],{"text":2167,"type":75,"marks":2168},"The Next Step: Scalable Yard Networks",[2169,2171],{"type":149,"attrs":2170},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2173,"content":2174},{"textAlign":139},[2175],{"text":2176,"type":75,"marks":2177},"Scalable yard networks are the next big thing. Solutions like Terminal's Yard Networks provide a comprehensive view of multiple facilities, allowing you to manage entire logistics systems from a central location. This network approach turns individual yards into interconnected points that can:",[2178],{"type":149,"attrs":2179},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":2181},[2182,2192,2202],{"type":1347,"content":2183},[2184],{"type":112,"attrs":2185,"content":2186},{"textAlign":139},[2187],{"text":2188,"type":75,"marks":2189},"Share data",[2190],{"type":149,"attrs":2191},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2193},[2194],{"type":112,"attrs":2195,"content":2196},{"textAlign":139},[2197],{"text":2198,"type":75,"marks":2199},"Balance workloads",[2200],{"type":149,"attrs":2201},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2203},[2204],{"type":112,"attrs":2205,"content":2206},{"textAlign":139},[2207],{"text":2208,"type":75,"marks":2209},"Coordinate asset movements across regions",[2210],{"type":149,"attrs":2211},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2213,"content":2214},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[2215],{"text":2216,"type":75,"marks":2217},"The Role of AI in Yard Management",[2218,2220],{"type":149,"attrs":2219},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2222,"content":2223},{"textAlign":139},[2224],{"text":2225,"type":75,"marks":2226},"You'll see AI systems making independent decisions about trailer positioning, gate prioritization, and resource deployment without human involvement. These advancements promise to:",[2227],{"type":149,"attrs":2228},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":2230},[2231,2241],{"type":1347,"content":2232},[2233],{"type":112,"attrs":2234,"content":2235},{"textAlign":139},[2236],{"text":2237,"type":75,"marks":2238},"Reduce asset search times by 90%",[2239],{"type":149,"attrs":2240},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":2242},[2243],{"type":112,"attrs":2244,"content":2245},{"textAlign":139},[2246],{"text":2247,"type":75,"marks":2248},"Cut driver detention fees by 12%",[2249],{"type":149,"attrs":2250},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2252,"content":2253},{"textAlign":139},[2254],{"text":2255,"type":75,"marks":2256},"These metrics will directly affect your profits and ability to operate in an increasingly complex supply chain environment.",[2257],{"type":149,"attrs":2258},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[2261],{"name":2262,"created_at":2263,"published_at":2264,"updated_at":2265,"id":2266,"uuid":2267,"content":2268,"slug":2278,"full_slug":2279,"sort_by_date":139,"position":2280,"tag_list":2281,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2282,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2283,"first_published_at":2284,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2285,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139,"_stopResolving":25},"Staff","2025-09-17T02:03:54.976Z","2025-09-17T02:21:11.655Z","2025-09-17T02:21:11.665Z",91689103296726,"489dfeeb-71d3-4812-95bb-a398f19766eb",{"bio":2269,"_uid":2270,"name":2271,"role":2272,"avatar":2273,"component":2277},"Coming together in collaboration, the staff of Terminal Industries unites diverse expertise in logistics, technology, and operations to deliver forward-thinking insights. As a collective, they are leaders in shaping the future of the yard with innovation and measurable impact. ","baebbf03-31b0-4c16-85de-89c04110c47e","Terminal Industries Staff","Terminal Team",{"id":2274,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2275,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2276,"is_external_url":49},91690297050938,"/storyblok/f/337048/420x420/2b235317ec/terminal-symbol-black.png",{},"Author","staff","authors/staff",-100,[],80896710863150,"ee586c2e-c58d-4b9e-a3db-8dbd88eaede3","2025-09-17T02:08:13.565Z",[],"The evolution of yard management systems is one of the most significant changes in logistics technology. In the past, traditional yard operations relied heavily on clipboards, paper logs, and manual tracking. This process was prone to human error, had limited visibility, and often faced operational bottlenecks. You may have experienced the frustration of misplaced trailers, delayed shipments, and hours wasted searching for assets in large facilities.\n","blog","Post",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2290},{},"From Manual to Autonomous: The Evolution of Yard Management Systems",{"id":2293,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2294,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2295,"is_external_url":49},110546175915420,"/storyblok/f/337048/796x418/e137c31024/f.webp",{},[],"Trace the evolution of yard management systems from manual processes to fully autonomous operations—and see how AI-native platforms are redefining speed, accuracy, and yard control.",{"value":2299,"plugin":2300},"#ABFF02","storyblok-palette","from-manual-to-autonomous-the-evolution-of-the-yard-management-system","all-resources/from-manual-to-autonomous-the-evolution-of-the-yard-management-system",-1070,[2305,2306,2307,2308],"ai","metrics","route optimization","technology",80887824638261,"8fceecbc-e385-4c4d-804e-11478df05bf8","2025-11-18T15:02:41.352Z",[],[2314],{"name":2262,"created_at":2263,"published_at":2264,"updated_at":2265,"id":2266,"uuid":2267,"content":2315,"slug":2278,"full_slug":2279,"sort_by_date":139,"position":2280,"tag_list":2318,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2282,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2283,"first_published_at":2284,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2319,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},{"bio":2269,"_uid":2270,"name":2271,"role":2272,"avatar":2316,"component":2277},{"id":2274,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2275,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2317,"is_external_url":49},{},[],[],[],{"age":2322,"cache-control":2323,"cf-cache-status":2324,"cf-ray":2325,"connection":2326,"content-type":2327,"date":2328,"etag":2329,"referrer-policy":2330,"sb-be-version":2331,"server":2332,"transfer-encoding":2333,"vary":2334,"via":2335,"x-amz-cf-id":2336,"x-amz-cf-pop":2337,"x-cache":2338,"x-content-type-options":2339,"x-frame-options":2340,"x-permitted-cross-domain-policies":2341,"x-request-id":2342,"x-runtime":2343,"x-xss-protection":2344},"26004","max-age=0, public, s-maxage=604800, stale-if-error=3600","DYNAMIC","a152efbdeabb347c-SIN","close","application/json; charset=utf-8","Fri, 03 Jul 2026 03:52:16 GMT","W/\"0e6a38fdfff61d7c3bd8eed463d982bd\"","strict-origin-when-cross-origin","5.899.0","cloudflare","chunked","Origin,Accept-Encoding","1.1 68203a043549f8c5af4f3da28709bcf6.cloudfront.net (CloudFront)","B35gmtGXYL126_fzu92gFjI_tFH7ACH2vEOfcR009FXHz7mh9FX-tg==","SIN2-P11","Hit from cloudfront","nosniff","SAMEORIGIN","none","58a95a38-8e48-4d0e-bbff-12592984b466","0.039158","0",[2346,2737,3033,3370,4345,5371,6307,7322,8183,8978,9871,11446,12609,13402,14326,15072,15876,16759,17467,18024,19139,19991,21019],{"name":2347,"created_at":2348,"published_at":2349,"updated_at":2350,"id":2351,"uuid":2352,"content":2353,"slug":2728,"full_slug":2729,"sort_by_date":139,"position":2730,"tag_list":2731,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":2734,"first_published_at":2735,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":2736,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"OCR Reads the Plate. Computer Vision Runs the Yard","2026-06-25T14:49:41.924Z","2026-06-25T16:55:39.874Z","2026-06-25T16:55:39.890Z",191321628389302,"962611ff-7a87-4bc7-a47a-c8d0b2938179",{"_uid":2354,"body":2355,"link":2711,"title":2712,"author":2713,"excerpt":2715,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":2716,"component":2288,"seo_image":2717,"seo_title":2719,"button_text":132,"cover_image":2720,"gated_asset":2724,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":2725,"background_color":2726,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"47caa694-c807-4eec-a112-c13dc425c1be",{"type":66,"content":2356},[2357,2365,2373,2381,2389,2397,2405,2413,2421,2429,2437,2451,2465,2479,2487,2495,2503,2511,2519,2527,2535,2543,2557,2571,2585,2599,2607,2615,2629,2643,2657,2671,2679,2687,2695,2703],{"type":112,"attrs":2358,"content":2359},{"textAlign":139},[2360],{"text":2361,"type":75,"marks":2362},"Walk a logistics buyer through three vendor demos this year and all three will say the same four words: \"AI-powered computer vision.\" A camera reads a license plate on the screen, a number populates a field, and everyone nods. It looks like the same technology.",[2363],{"type":149,"attrs":2364},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2366,"content":2367},{"textAlign":139},[2368],{"text":2369,"type":75,"marks":2370},"It isn't. And the gap between what those demos are actually doing is the difference between a faster clipboard and a system that runs your yard.",[2371],{"type":149,"attrs":2372},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2374,"content":2375},{"textAlign":139},[2376],{"text":2377,"type":75,"marks":2378},"Most of what gets sold as \"vision at the gate\" is optical character recognition. OCR is real, it's useful, and it's also forty years old. Terminal does something categorically different. Understanding why matters, because the buyers who can't tell the two apart are the ones who write off \"computer vision\" after a disappointing pilot, when what disappointed them was never computer vision at all.",[2379],{"type":149,"attrs":2380},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2382,"content":2383},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2384],{"text":2385,"type":75,"marks":2386},"What OCR actually does, and where it stops",[2387],{"type":149,"attrs":2388},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2390,"content":2391},{"textAlign":139},[2392],{"text":2393,"type":75,"marks":2394},"OCR has one job: turn a picture of text into a string of characters. Point it at a license plate and it gives you the plate number. Point it at a trailer and it reads the ID stenciled on the door. That's it. That's the entire capability.",[2395],{"type":149,"attrs":2396},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2398,"content":2399},{"textAlign":139},[2400],{"text":2401,"type":75,"marks":2402},"It's the same technology that scans a check or digitizes a paper form, aimed at a truck. When a gate vendor says \"our camera reads the plate,\" they are describing OCR, and they are describing the ceiling of what the system can do, not the floor.",[2403],{"type":149,"attrs":2404},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2406,"content":2407},{"textAlign":139},[2408],{"text":2409,"type":75,"marks":2410},"Here is the part the demo doesn't show you. After OCR reads the characters, a human still has to do everything that matters. Is this truck on today's appointment list? Which dock is open? Is the carrier legitimate? Is that a trailer or a container, and does it need fuel or a power connection? Is there fresh damage on the panel? OCR can't answer any of that. It hands you a number and walks away. Your guard, your dispatcher, and your clerk pick up exactly where they always did.",[2411],{"type":149,"attrs":2412},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2414,"content":2415},{"textAlign":139},[2416],{"text":2417,"type":75,"marks":2418},"That's why so many \"smart gates\" don't feel smart. They digitized the slowest keystroke at the gate and left the actual work untouched. You replaced a guard writing a plate on a clipboard with a camera writing a plate to a database. Faster data entry is not a transformed yard.",[2419],{"type":149,"attrs":2420},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2422,"content":2423},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2424],{"text":2425,"type":75,"marks":2426},"What Terminal does that OCR can't",[2427],{"type":149,"attrs":2428},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2430,"content":2431},{"textAlign":139},[2432],{"text":2433,"type":75,"marks":2434},"Terminal's computer vision is built in three layers. OCR is one small piece of the first one.",[2435],{"type":149,"attrs":2436},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2438,"content":2439},{"textAlign":139},[2440,2446],{"text":2441,"type":75,"marks":2442},"It reads.",[2443,2445],{"type":149,"attrs":2444},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2447,"type":75,"marks":2448}," Yes, Terminal captures the text: license plate, USDOT and motor carrier number, VIN, and trailer, container, and chassis IDs. This is the part that looks like OCR, except it runs against the industry's largest yard-specific data models and lands above 50% improvement over manual capture, which is why Ryder's Karen Jones called the accuracy \"a significant milestone in the race to modernize the yard.\" No RFID, no BLE tags, no specialized rigs. Off-the-shelf cameras, because the intelligence lives in the software, not on the pole.",[2449],{"type":149,"attrs":2450},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2452,"content":2453},{"textAlign":139},[2454,2460],{"text":2455,"type":75,"marks":2456},"It classifies and understands the scene.",[2457,2459],{"type":149,"attrs":2458},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2461,"type":75,"marks":2462}," This is where OCR ends and computer vision begins. Terminal doesn't just read characters, it identifies what it's looking at. Trailer versus container versus chassis. Container size and type. Class and fuel type. Carrier logos. Seal presence and seal number. The operating state of a reefer unit, set temperature and current reading off the display. The condition of the asset on the way in. OCR sees a string. Terminal sees the truck, the trailer, the load, and the state they're all in, and it understands that scene the way an experienced yard worker would, every time, on every lane, without getting tired at shift change.",[2463],{"type":149,"attrs":2464},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2466,"content":2467},{"textAlign":139},[2468,2474],{"text":2469,"type":75,"marks":2470},"It acts.",[2471,2473],{"type":149,"attrs":2472},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2475,"type":75,"marks":2476}," A read and a classification are still just data until something happens. Terminal turns what it sees into the next move automatically. If the truck matches the appointment and the carrier clears, the gate opens and the trailer registers as on-yard. If the carrier's risk score says hold, the truck is stopped before the arm ever lifts. A reefer below its fuel threshold doesn't get admitted. A container gets routed differently than a trailer, with the right yard action surfaced for the right asset in the right spot. We connect these into what we call Missions: multi-step, traceable movements from gate to dock that the system orchestrates on its own.",[2477],{"type":149,"attrs":2478},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2480,"content":2481},{"textAlign":139},[2482],{"text":2483,"type":75,"marks":2484},"OCR gives you a record. Terminal makes a decision.",[2485],{"type":149,"attrs":2486},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2488,"content":2489},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2490],{"text":2491,"type":75,"marks":2492},"The difference, in one line",[2493],{"type":149,"attrs":2494},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2496,"content":2497},{"textAlign":139},[2498],{"text":2499,"type":75,"marks":2500},"Legacy systems, and the OCR-at-the-gate tools bolted onto them, record what already happened. Terminal orchestrates what happens next.",[2501],{"type":149,"attrs":2502},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2504,"content":2505},{"textAlign":139},[2506],{"text":2507,"type":75,"marks":2508},"OCR is the purest example of recording. It is, quite literally, a machine for writing down what it saw. That has value, the way a faster typist has value. But it leaves you reactive. You still find out about the problem after the truck is inside the fence, after the wrong trailer left the dock, after the reefer drifted out of range, after the fraudulent carrier drove off with the load.",[2509],{"type":149,"attrs":2510},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2512,"content":2513},{"textAlign":139},[2514],{"text":2515,"type":75,"marks":2516},"As we put it when we launched our security layer: a fraudulent carrier at the gate at 9:14 AM is not a ticket to be reviewed later. It is a decision that has to be made before the gate arm opens. OCR can write down that the truck arrived. Only a system that sees, understands, and acts can stop it.",[2517],{"type":149,"attrs":2518},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2520,"content":2521},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2522],{"text":2523,"type":75,"marks":2524},"The hard part isn't the vision. It's operationalizing it.",[2525],{"type":149,"attrs":2526},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2528,"content":2529},{"textAlign":139},[2530],{"text":2531,"type":75,"marks":2532},"Here's the fair objection a sharp buyer raises next: if reading, classifying, and acting is the bar, couldn't any computer vision vendor clear it? In a demo, maybe. In a live yard, across hundreds of sites, in the rain, at 2 AM, on every asset that rolls in, it's a different problem entirely. Operationalizing computer vision for the yard is where the real difference lives, and it's the part you can't see in a slide.",[2533],{"type":149,"attrs":2534},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2536,"content":2537},{"textAlign":139},[2538],{"text":2539,"type":75,"marks":2540},"Four things make Terminal's vision work in the field, not just in the deck.",[2541],{"type":149,"attrs":2542},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2544,"content":2545},{"textAlign":139},[2546,2552],{"text":2547,"type":75,"marks":2548},"The models keep getting better.",[2549,2551],{"type":149,"attrs":2550},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2553,"type":75,"marks":2554}," A computer vision system you install is a system that starts aging the day it goes live. Ours is the opposite. We are constantly training and updating our models, so accuracy improves and the range of what the system can recognize and act on expands over time. The yard you deploy this quarter is running a more capable system next quarter, with no forklift upgrade.",[2555],{"type":149,"attrs":2556},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2558,"content":2559},{"textAlign":139},[2560,2566],{"text":2561,"type":75,"marks":2562},"It tunes to your yard, not a generic one.",[2563,2565],{"type":149,"attrs":2564},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2567,"type":75,"marks":2568}," No two yards are the same. Layouts, lighting, lane configurations, asset mix, regional plates, and local quirks all differ, and a frozen one-size-fits-all model breaks on the exceptions, which in a yard is most of the day. Terminal's vision system adapts and tunes to the specific conditions and use cases in the field, so it performs on your operation as it actually runs, not on the clean version in a brochure.",[2569],{"type":149,"attrs":2570},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2572,"content":2573},{"textAlign":139},[2574,2580],{"text":2575,"type":75,"marks":2576},"It's one vision system used many ways, not a pile of point tools.",[2577,2579],{"type":149,"attrs":2578},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2581,"type":75,"marks":2582}," This is the part competitors can't reverse-engineer from a feature list. Terminal's gate capture, real-time location across the yard, and perimeter security are not three products from three vendors stitched together. They are the same vision system applied to different jobs, sharing one data model and one source of truth. The plate the gate read is the same asset that RTLS is locating and the same one security is watching. Buy three point solutions and you get three silos that don't talk to each other. Build on Terminal and every capability inherits from the same vision layer, which is exactly why the system interlocks instead of leaking at the seams.",[2583],{"type":149,"attrs":2584},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2586,"content":2587},{"textAlign":139},[2588,2594],{"text":2589,"type":75,"marks":2590},"We know the yard.",[2591,2593],{"type":149,"attrs":2592},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2595,"type":75,"marks":2596}," This is not a science project. The hardest part of putting AI vision into a yard isn't the AI, it's knowing what a yard actually does: how drop-and-hook differs from a live load, why a spotter move happens when it does, what a gate guard is really checking for. Terminal pairs deep vision and AI engineering with deep logistics operating experience across the whole company, from development and engineering to go-to-market, deployment, and support. We were founded by operators (Ryder, NFI, Lineage, and Prologis) for exactly that reason. The vision technology is necessary. Knowing the yard is what makes it work.",[2597],{"type":149,"attrs":2598},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2600,"content":2601},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2602],{"text":2603,"type":75,"marks":2604},"What this translates to in the yard",[2605],{"type":149,"attrs":2606},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2608,"content":2609},{"textAlign":139},[2610],{"text":2611,"type":75,"marks":2612},"The category difference shows up as business value in four places an operator can actually measure.",[2613],{"type":149,"attrs":2614},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2616,"content":2617},{"textAlign":139},[2618,2624],{"text":2619,"type":75,"marks":2620},"Speed and throughput.",[2621,2623],{"type":149,"attrs":2622},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2625,"type":75,"marks":2626}," Vision capture and automated check-in move a truck through the gate in seconds instead of the fourteen minutes a manual gate averages. Multiply that across every arrival and you cut dwell, shrink detention exposure, and turn the yard faster without adding a lane or a clerk.",[2627],{"type":149,"attrs":2628},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2630,"content":2631},{"textAlign":139},[2632,2638],{"text":2633,"type":75,"marks":2634},"Labor.",[2635,2637],{"type":149,"attrs":2636},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2639,"type":75,"marks":2640}," Computer vision does the work people used to do on foot. The system always knows what's in the yard and where it sits, so your team stops walking the lot to count assets, and the gate, dispatch, and yard-check roles that OCR left fully staffed start to come down.",[2641],{"type":149,"attrs":2642},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2644,"content":2645},{"textAlign":139},[2646,2652],{"text":2647,"type":75,"marks":2648},"Errors and claims.",[2649,2651],{"type":149,"attrs":2650},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2653,"type":75,"marks":2654}," Reading the plate right is table stakes. Confirming the right trailer is at the right door with the right freight before it moves is what prevents mis-ships, OS&D claims, and broken chain of custody. Classification and verification do that. OCR doesn't.",[2655],{"type":149,"attrs":2656},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2658,"content":2659},{"textAlign":139},[2660,2666],{"text":2661,"type":75,"marks":2662},"Fraud and compliance.",[2663,2665],{"type":149,"attrs":2664},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2667,"type":75,"marks":2668}," Carrier risk gets scored before the truck arrives. Driver identity gets matched to the appointment. Conveyance condition and seal numbers get captured as a timestamped, photo-backed record, the kind of CTPAT-grade inspection most yards still do on paper, if they do it at all. That record is the difference between defending a claim and eating it.",[2669],{"type":149,"attrs":2670},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2672,"content":2673},{"textAlign":139},[2674],{"text":2675,"type":75,"marks":2676},"Across these, the outcome our customers see is 4x or more ROI inside the first year, on a platform that goes live in as little as five days. You don't get that from reading characters faster. You get it from a system that runs the yard.",[2677],{"type":149,"attrs":2678},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":2680,"content":2681},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[2682],{"text":2683,"type":75,"marks":2684},"The takeaway for buyers",[2685],{"type":149,"attrs":2686},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2688,"content":2689},{"textAlign":139},[2690],{"text":2691,"type":75,"marks":2692},"Stop evaluating gate cameras on whether they can read a plate. They all can, more or less, and reading the plate was never the hard part.",[2693],{"type":149,"attrs":2694},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2696,"content":2697},{"textAlign":139},[2698],{"text":2699,"type":75,"marks":2700},"Start asking the question that separates a faster clipboard from a transformed operation: after the camera reads it, who decides, and who acts? If the answer is still your guard, your dispatcher, and your clerk, you bought OCR. If the answer is the system itself, you bought computer vision.",[2701],{"type":149,"attrs":2702},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2704,"content":2705},{"textAlign":139},[2706],{"text":2707,"type":75,"marks":2708},"That's the line. And it's the whole game.",[2709],{"type":149,"attrs":2710},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},"OCR Reads the Plate, Computer Vision Runs the Yard.",[2714],"4970a15a-a518-4e01-a0de-cb3b272e0fe4","OCR (the \"AI camera\" most gate vendors actually sell) just reads characters into a string and hands the work back to your guard, dispatcher, and clerk, which is why a faster clipboard never transforms a yard. Terminal's computer vision reads, then classifies and understands the whole scene, then acts on it (open the gate, hold the fraudulent carrier, route the reefer), turning recorded data into orchestrated decisions worth 4x ROI in year one.","Why \"we use AI cameras at the gate\" can mean two completely different things, and why the difference is the whole game.",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2718},{},"OCR vs. Computer Vision in the Yard | Terminal Industries",{"id":2721,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":2722,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":2723,"is_external_url":49},191336446793782,"/storyblok/f/337048/1510x980/058e2ef5d7/computer-vision-at-gate.png",{},[],"Most \"AI gate cameras\" are just OCR reading a plate. See how Terminal's computer vision reads, understands, and acts to run the yard, not just record it.",{"value":2727,"plugin":2300},"#c2c2c2","ocr-reads-the-plate-computer-vision-runs-the-yard","all-resources/ocr-reads-the-plate-computer-vision-runs-the-yard",-2350,[2305,2732,2308,2733],"computer vision","yms","9165d819-e166-4d42-bfeb-8c26ff721b22","2026-06-25T15:52:43.238Z",[],{"name":2738,"created_at":2739,"published_at":2740,"updated_at":2741,"id":2742,"uuid":2743,"content":2744,"slug":3026,"full_slug":3027,"sort_by_date":139,"position":3028,"tag_list":3029,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":3030,"first_published_at":3031,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":3032,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"The CV market is having its SaaSpocalypse moment","2026-06-22T16:34:08.111Z","2026-06-25T15:55:53.059Z","2026-06-25T15:55:53.075Z",190285611491708,"e185b904-4a08-41d4-8db2-03829cffc791",{"_uid":2745,"body":2746,"link":3011,"title":3012,"author":3013,"excerpt":3015,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2288,"seo_image":3016,"seo_title":3018,"button_text":132,"cover_image":3019,"gated_asset":3023,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":3024,"background_color":3025,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"836efd9f-94df-4e48-84c7-5171d2e725ed",{"type":66,"content":2747},[2748,2756,2764,2772,2780,2788,2797,2811,2819,2832,2840,2853,2870,2879,2887,2895,2916,2925,2933,2942,2950,2959,2967,2979,2987,2995,3003],{"type":112,"attrs":2749,"content":2750},{"textAlign":139},[2751],{"text":2752,"type":75,"marks":2753},"Depending on who has a vested stake, the \"SaaSpocalypse\" may or may not happen. We've seen traditional enterprise B2B SaaS companies move fast to deploy new AI solutions, even when they're bolted on after the fact.",[2754],{"type":149,"attrs":2755},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2757,"content":2758},{"textAlign":139},[2759],{"text":2760,"type":75,"marks":2761},"Supply chain is no different. Legacy tech providers are shipping chatbots (glorified AI, if we're honest), and I'm sure some customers have found value in them.",[2762],{"type":149,"attrs":2763},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2765,"content":2766},{"textAlign":139},[2767],{"text":2768,"type":75,"marks":2769},"What hasn't changed across any industry is the underlying business model. Customers of every size are still forced to buy overpriced software packages with 50+ features and modules when they need two or three for their specific job. The cost of traditional SaaS, plus the lengthy implementation schedules and fees that come with it, is actively holding everyone back from adopting the latest technology, from supply chain VPs to 3PLs.",[2770],{"type":149,"attrs":2771},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2773,"content":2774},{"textAlign":139},[2775],{"text":2776,"type":75,"marks":2777},"With AI-native alternatives, the need to buy a massive package with a massive price tag no longer serves the market. Compounding this is the terrible user experience; once you’ve used an AI-native platform, the experience of trying to manage critical tasks through a bolt-on is painful. That's the genesis of the SaaSpocalypse.",[2778],{"type":149,"attrs":2779},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2781,"content":2782},{"textAlign":139},[2783],{"text":2784,"type":75,"marks":2785},"I'd argue computer vision is heading for the same reckoning. CV players burst onto the scene over the last decade and priced their starting packages in the six figures. But the price of computer vision has not kept pace with the rate of technological development, as hardware got cheaper, models got better, and the cost to deploy decreased significantly.",[2786],{"type":149,"attrs":2787},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2789,"content":2790},{"textAlign":139},[2791],{"text":2792,"type":75,"marks":2793},"So why does CV still cost what it costs? It doesn't have to. Four things changed underneath the market, and legacy pricing never caught up.",[2794,2796],{"type":149,"attrs":2795},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2798,"content":2799},{"textAlign":139},[2800,2806],{"text":2801,"type":75,"marks":2802},"Change 1: The architecture is AI-native, not retrofitted.",[2803,2805],{"type":149,"attrs":2804},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2807,"type":75,"marks":2808}," ",[2809],{"type":149,"attrs":2810},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2812,"content":2813},{"textAlign":139},[2814],{"text":2815,"type":75,"marks":2816},"Legacy vendors built their platforms in a pre-AI world and have spent years grafting intelligence onto an old foundation. Every bolt-on carries a cost, and that cost gets passed to you as the buyer. When a provider is able to build for AI from the ground up, the economics start in a completely different place.",[2817],{"type":149,"attrs":2818},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2820,"content":2821},{"textAlign":139},[2822,2828],{"text":2823,"type":75,"marks":2824},"Change 2: The pricing is as-a-service, not perpetual license plus fees.",[2825,2827],{"type":149,"attrs":2826},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2807,"type":75,"marks":2829},[2830],{"type":149,"attrs":2831},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2833,"content":2834},{"textAlign":139},[2835],{"text":2836,"type":75,"marks":2837},"You shouldn't pay six figures up front for capabilities you haven't used yet. As-a-service pricing ties what you spend to the value you get, and it kills the implementation tax that has padded CV invoices for a decade.",[2838],{"type":149,"attrs":2839},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2841,"content":2842},{"textAlign":139},[2843,2849],{"text":2844,"type":75,"marks":2845},"Change 3: The models are better, and better is cheaper.",[2846,2848],{"type":149,"attrs":2847},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":2807,"type":75,"marks":2850},[2851],{"type":149,"attrs":2852},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2854,"content":2855},{"textAlign":139},[2856,2865],{"text":2857,"type":75,"marks":2858},"Modern CV models ",[2859,2863],{"type":2087,"attrs":2860},{"href":2861,"uuid":258,"anchor":139,"target":2862,"linktype":19},"/terminal-ai-computer-vision","_self",{"type":149,"attrs":2864},{"color":1233},{"text":2866,"type":75,"marks":2867},"deliver higher accuracy per dollar of compute than the hand-tuned, bespoke systems of the 2010s, and the capability gap is widening in the buyer's favor every quarter.",[2868],{"type":149,"attrs":2869},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2871,"content":2872},{"textAlign":139},[2873],{"text":2874,"type":75,"marks":2875},"Change 4: Hardware is more accessible than ever",[2876,2878],{"type":149,"attrs":2877},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2880,"content":2881},{"textAlign":139},[2882],{"text":2883,"type":75,"marks":2884},"You no longer need specialized, expensive camera rigs to run serious computer vision. Off-the-shelf cameras and edge compute do the work, because the intelligence lives in the software. The expensive part of CV is no longer the part you bolt to a pole.",[2885],{"type":149,"attrs":2886},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2888,"content":2889},{"textAlign":139},[2890],{"text":2891,"type":75,"marks":2892},"Put those four together and the math is simple. We can deliver computer vision that's priced for ROI, well below what's on the market and twice as powerful, because the cost structure underneath it has fundamentally changed.",[2893],{"type":149,"attrs":2894},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2896,"content":2897},{"textAlign":139},[2898,2903,2911],{"text":2899,"type":75,"marks":2900},"This is an interesting dichotomy, because the generation of CV solutions offer premium features and returns, but at an affordable price point. ",[2901],{"type":149,"attrs":2902},{"color":1233},{"text":2904,"type":75,"marks":2905},"The ROI is demonstrable ",[2906,2909],{"type":2087,"attrs":2907},{"href":2908,"uuid":735,"anchor":139,"target":2862,"linktype":19},"/yard-efficiency-calculator",{"type":149,"attrs":2910},{"color":1233},{"text":2912,"type":75,"marks":2913},"and it shows up in – yet again – four distinct places an operator can measure:  ",[2914],{"type":149,"attrs":2915},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2917,"content":2918},{"textAlign":139},[2919],{"text":2920,"type":75,"marks":2921},"Speed",[2922,2924],{"type":149,"attrs":2923},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2926,"content":2927},{"textAlign":139},[2928],{"text":2929,"type":75,"marks":2930},"Vision capture and automated check-in move a truck through the gate in seconds instead of minutes. Multiply that across every arrival and you cut dwell, shrink detention exposure, and turn the yard faster without adding a lane or a clerk. Not to mention the opportunity to replace RFID solutions. ",[2931],{"type":149,"attrs":2932},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2934,"content":2935},{"textAlign":139},[2936],{"text":2937,"type":75,"marks":2938},"Labor",[2939,2941],{"type":149,"attrs":2940},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2943,"content":2944},{"textAlign":139},[2945],{"text":2946,"type":75,"marks":2947},"Computer vision does the work people used to do on foot. The system always knows what's in the yard and where it sits, so your team doesn’t manage millions of inventory by walking around the lot. ",[2948],{"type":149,"attrs":2949},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2951,"content":2952},{"textAlign":139},[2953],{"text":2954,"type":75,"marks":2955},"Error reduction",[2956,2958],{"type":149,"attrs":2957},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2960,"content":2961},{"textAlign":139},[2962],{"text":2963,"type":75,"marks":2964},"Load verification confirms the right trailer is at the right door with the right freight before it moves. That means fewer mis-ships, fewer OS&D claims, and a secure chain of custody. ",[2965],{"type":149,"attrs":2966},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2968,"content":2969},{"textAlign":139},[2970],{"text":2971,"type":75,"marks":2972},"Fines and fraud",[2973,2976,2978],{"type":2087,"attrs":2974},{"href":2975,"uuid":285,"anchor":139,"target":2862,"linktype":19},"/yard-security",{"type":149,"attrs":2977},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":2980,"content":2981},{"textAlign":139},[2982],{"text":2983,"type":75,"marks":2984},"D&D charges get slashed when trucks can move quickly and efficiently through the lot, compliance exposure decreases when every move is CTPAT compliant, and carrier verification happens even before the truck arrives, and before the load is stolen. ",[2985],{"type":149,"attrs":2986},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2988,"content":2989},{"textAlign":139},[2990],{"text":2991,"type":75,"marks":2992},"It makes no sense for buyers to keep accepting legacy CV that's priced and built like the enterprise SaaS of the 2010s.",[2993],{"type":149,"attrs":2994},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":2996,"content":2997},{"textAlign":139},[2998],{"text":2999,"type":75,"marks":3000},"We're in a new era, and technology buyers deserve better ROI on their investment. That means affordable computer vision that's part of the yard platform you already run, working the gate, the lanes, and the dock instead of sitting in a separate six-figure silo.",[3001],{"type":149,"attrs":3002},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3004,"content":3005},{"textAlign":139},[3006],{"text":3007,"type":75,"marks":3008},"I'm a longtime SaaS veteran, and what I'm seeing in the CV market has me excited for the value this new generation of tools will deliver, at a price point that finally makes sense.",[3009],{"type":149,"attrs":3010},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},"The CV Market is Having its SaaSpocalypse Moment",[3014],"677433e4-2813-4ca0-b483-977bdd535709","Computer vision is still priced like 2010s enterprise software: six figures up front, long implementations, and a point tool you manage on the side. The economics underneath it have shifted, so Terminal delivers CV at a price built for ROI, folded into the yard platform you already run rather than bolted on beside it.",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3017},{},"The CV Market Is Having Its SaaSpocalypse Moment",{"id":3020,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":3021,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3022,"is_external_url":49},190290056574799,"/storyblok/f/337048/628x318/b8322ea2bb/computer-vision-ubiquity.jpeg",{},[],"Legacy computer vision is priced like 2010s enterprise SaaS. Four shifts changed the math. Here's why CV should cost less and live inside your yard platform.",{"value":2299,"plugin":2300},"the-cv-market-is-having-its-saaspocalypse-moment","all-resources/the-cv-market-is-having-its-saaspocalypse-moment",-2340,[2305,2732,2308,2733],"2e890c29-4787-457f-a19d-596e79539bf1","2026-06-22T16:57:40.535Z",[],{"name":3034,"created_at":3035,"published_at":3036,"updated_at":3037,"id":3038,"uuid":3039,"content":3040,"slug":3360,"full_slug":3361,"sort_by_date":139,"position":3362,"tag_list":3363,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":3367,"first_published_at":3368,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":3369,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"If trust in freight is dead, why is it still running the yard?","2026-06-17T23:32:37.997Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.455Z","2026-06-17T23:46:56.471Z",188618989585127,"2202c3e1-77d8-4df4-bda3-fded1fb95034",{"_uid":3041,"body":3042,"link":3347,"title":3034,"author":3348,"excerpt":3349,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2288,"seo_image":3350,"seo_title":3352,"button_text":132,"cover_image":3353,"gated_asset":3357,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":3358,"background_color":3359,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"2e214bba-8b06-4181-85d1-edd14859a052",{"type":66,"content":3043},[3044,3052,3060,3139,3147,3155,3163,3171,3179,3187,3195,3203,3211,3219,3227,3235,3243,3251,3259,3267,3275,3283,3291,3299,3307,3315,3323,3331,3339],{"type":112,"attrs":3045,"content":3046},{"textAlign":139},[3047],{"text":3048,"type":75,"marks":3049},"I’ve been in the supply chain industry for 30 years. For the past decade or so, as new software solutions flooded the market, anyone who knew “how things really operated,” knew it was an industry run on relationships. Technology was just a supplement to how money, data and freight got moved from A to B. Even with our current AI gold rush, there are still industry veterans who remember faxing bills of lading and are still working with those same colleagues. I’d argue the foundation of the industry – trust, mutual respect, familiarity – has eroded to a point of no return. Not because of technology, but because of prolific freight fraud that has fostered a culture of paranoia across the industry. And as a veteran of yard technology and systems, I can tell you a lot of this distrust starts in the yard. ",[3050],{"type":149,"attrs":3051},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3053,"content":3054},{"textAlign":139},[3055],{"text":3056,"type":75,"marks":3057},"Walk into almost any logistics facility in the country and you'll find the same scene at the gate: a person with a tablet or a clipboard. They typically don’t have any information on the trucks coming in – is this the carrier we booked? Is this driver legit? Is that the right trailer, sealed the way it left the last yard? Security and visibility solutions have helped operators answer those questions across almost every node of the supply chain, but in the yard, carrier verification and security is about as sophisticated as the check out process at Costco. ",[3058],{"type":149,"attrs":3059},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3061,"content":3062},{"textAlign":139},[3063,3068,3079,3084,3093,3098,3106,3111,3120,3125,3134],{"text":3064,"type":75,"marks":3065},"Cargo theft across the U.S. and Canada ",[3066],{"type":149,"attrs":3067},{"color":1233},{"text":3069,"type":75,"marks":3070},"climbed past $725 million last year",[3071,3074,3077],{"type":2087,"attrs":3072},{"href":3073,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.cargonet.com/news-and-events/cargonet-in-the-media/2025-theft-trends/",{"type":149,"attrs":3075},{"color":3076},"#1155CC",{"type":3078},"underline",{"text":3080,"type":75,"marks":3081},", a 60% jump, and the fastest-growing vector isn't the smash-and-grab. It's ",[3082],{"type":149,"attrs":3083},{"color":1233},{"text":3085,"type":75,"marks":3086},"fraud",[3087,3090,3092],{"type":2087,"attrs":3088},{"href":3089,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ic3.gov/PSA/2026/PSA260430",{"type":149,"attrs":3091},{"color":3076},{"type":3078},{"text":3094,"type":75,"marks":3095},": fictitious pickups, stolen identities, carriers that look legitimate on a load board and vanish with a full trailer. The FBI has ",[3096],{"type":149,"attrs":3097},{"color":1233},{"text":3099,"type":75,"marks":3100},"said plainly",[3101,3103,3105],{"type":2087,"attrs":3102},{"href":3089,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},{"type":149,"attrs":3104},{"color":3076},{"type":3078},{"text":3107,"type":75,"marks":3108}," that impersonation is now the dominant way freight gets stolen. And people like the veteran gate guard who knew every regular driver by name is retiring. ",[3109],{"type":149,"attrs":3110},{"color":1233},{"text":3112,"type":75,"marks":3113},"Warehouse turnover sits near 50%",[3114,3117,3119],{"type":2087,"attrs":3115},{"href":3116,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.bls.gov/news.release/pdf/jolts.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":3118},{"color":3076},{"type":3078},{"text":3121,"type":75,"marks":3122},"; for long-haul drivers it's",[3123],{"type":149,"attrs":3124},{"color":1233},{"text":3126,"type":75,"marks":3127}," above 90%",[3128,3131,3133],{"type":2087,"attrs":3129},{"href":3130,"uuid":139,"anchor":139,"target":139,"linktype":96},"https://www.ooida.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/The-Churn-A-Brief-Look-at-the-Roots-of-High-Driver-Turnover-in-U.S.-Trucking.pdf",{"type":149,"attrs":3132},{"color":3076},{"type":3078},{"text":3135,"type":75,"marks":3136},". ",[3137],{"type":149,"attrs":3138},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3140,"content":3141},{"textAlign":139},[3142],{"text":3143,"type":75,"marks":3144},"So we have a place where every load in the supply chain physically changes hands, where legal custody transfers, where accurate information is scarce or absent, where information asymmetry is accelerating fraud, and where the human safety net is thinning. And it remains the one part of the chain we never really invested in. Go figure. ",[3145],{"type":149,"attrs":3146},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3148,"content":3149},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3150],{"text":3151,"type":75,"marks":3152},"Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem ",[3153],{"type":149,"attrs":3154},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3156,"content":3157},{"textAlign":139},[3158],{"text":3159,"type":75,"marks":3160},"When a load is stolen through fraud, the strategic theft completes at the moment the trailer is released. The facility that released it is the one left holding the liability. The contractual and compliance obligations that increasingly govern freight (documented carrier vetting, verified driver identity, conveyance inspection, an unbroken chain-of-custody record) all point back to the gate that let the truck through.",[3161],{"type":149,"attrs":3162},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3164,"content":3165},{"textAlign":139},[3166],{"text":3167,"type":75,"marks":3168},"Today, cargo insurers, customer contracts, and programs like CTPAT increasingly demand records that paper-based yards cannot produce, and that a gate workforce turning over every eighteen months cannot reliably capture by hand. Yard security is, in fact, the warehouse’s problem, and it has to be solved at the gate, inside the system that runs it, because that's where custody actually changes and where the record either gets made or gets lost.",[3169],{"type":149,"attrs":3170},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3172,"content":3173},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3174],{"text":3175,"type":75,"marks":3176},"No one owns the yard (and that’s a problem)",[3177],{"type":149,"attrs":3178},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3180,"content":3181},{"textAlign":139},[3182],{"text":3183,"type":75,"marks":3184},"I got my first IT job at a 3PL in the early 1990s. It's tempting to say the yard security problem is about bad software, that the industry tried to secure the yard and the tools weren't good enough. But back then the operations team was more worried about people jumping the fence, cutting the seal, and throwing product back over. Technology wasn't available, so companies threw bodies at it.",[3185],{"type":149,"attrs":3186},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3188,"content":3189},{"textAlign":139},[3190],{"text":3191,"type":75,"marks":3192},"Yard management software was built for operations and throughput: dock assignments, dwell time, trailer locations, getting trucks in and out efficiently. Security, identity, and chain of custody were understood as separate concerns, owned by separate people, and addressed, when they were addressed at all, by separate means. This is why most facilities outsource the gate to a security company. Some of it got handled by point solutions bolted on from the outside: carrier-vetting services, cameras, physical ID checks by a guy named Steve. A lot of it wasn't handled by software at all.",[3193],{"type":149,"attrs":3194},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3196,"content":3197},{"textAlign":139},[3198],{"text":3199,"type":75,"marks":3200},"The result is a set of capabilities that have always lived in paper documentation and verbal communication over a radio – silos – disconnected from each other and from the system that actually runs the yard. For example, the camera never knew who the driver was, the carrier check never reached the gate, and the custody record, where it existed, sat in a binder. None of these pieces were wrong on their own. They simply were never brought together, because for most of the industry's history there was no obvious reason to make changes. ",[3201],{"type":149,"attrs":3202},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3204,"content":3205},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3206],{"text":3207,"type":75,"marks":3208},"The lesser of two evils",[3209],{"type":149,"attrs":3210},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3212,"content":3213},{"textAlign":139},[3214],{"text":3215,"type":75,"marks":3216},"For most of its history, buying yard technology meant choosing between two unsatisfying options, and the choice had nothing to do with security. It was just the shape of the market.",[3217],{"type":149,"attrs":3218},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3220,"content":3221},{"textAlign":139},[3222],{"text":3223,"type":75,"marks":3224},"The first option was the large enterprise platform that promised end-to-end control of everything. In practice it was a clunky, glorified system of record: an expensive license, a six month deployment, zero flexibility. It promised comprehensive coverage yet could not change with the business without a massive change request and a matching invoice. You got breadth, and you paid for it in cost and rigidity.",[3225],{"type":149,"attrs":3226},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3228,"content":3229},{"textAlign":139},[3230],{"text":3231,"type":75,"marks":3232},"The second was the point solution, with the opposite promise: do one thing exceptionally well. Many genuinely deliver. But when every capability comes from a different vendor, the buyer inherits subscriptions, logins, dashboards, data formats, and renewal cycles, none of which speak to one another. Someone has to integrate them, monitor them, reconcile their outputs, and re-buy them every year. You got depth, and you paid for it in fragmentation.",[3233],{"type":149,"attrs":3234},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3236,"content":3237},{"textAlign":139},[3238],{"text":3239,"type":75,"marks":3240},"So that was the trade. Breadth or depth. One expensive, rigid system or ten sharp tools that don't talk. For decades there was no third answer, and no reason to expect one.",[3241],{"type":149,"attrs":3242},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3244,"content":3245},{"textAlign":139},[3246],{"text":3247,"type":75,"marks":3248},"AI-native development is the third answer. Capabilities that once demanded a specialized enterprise stack and a year of integration can now be built and deployed in a fraction of the time, at a fraction of the cost. You no longer choose between breadth and depth, or between flexibility and cohesion. You can have technology that does many things at once, changes with the business, and doesn't break the bank or trigger a year of change management.",[3249],{"type":149,"attrs":3250},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3252,"content":3253},{"textAlign":139},[3254],{"text":3255,"type":75,"marks":3256},"That is what makes this moment matter for the yard. Once the tradeoff collapses, capabilities that used to demand entirely separate systems can finally live in one. And the two that most need to come together are yard management and yard security, domains that were always treated as separate concerns, owned by separate people, bought from separate vendors. For the first time, there is no reason they have to be.",[3257],{"type":149,"attrs":3258},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3260,"content":3261},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3262],{"text":3263,"type":75,"marks":3264},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate ",[3265],{"type":149,"attrs":3266},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3268,"content":3269},{"textAlign":139},[3270],{"text":3271,"type":75,"marks":3272},"For the first time, the technology exists to create a modular layer inside the system that already runs the yard. The capabilities that secure a yard (knowing the carrier, verifying the driver, watching the perimeter, documenting what actually leaves) no longer have to be a stack of disconnected point tools or a separate enterprise security program.",[3273],{"type":149,"attrs":3274},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3276,"content":3277},{"textAlign":139},[3278],{"text":3279,"type":75,"marks":3280},"We’re seeing a great convergence: yard security and yard management becoming one single entity. And AI has made it feasible to build something modular and affordable that does both at once.",[3281],{"type":149,"attrs":3282},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3284,"content":3285},{"textAlign":139},[3286],{"text":3287,"type":75,"marks":3288},"Secondarily, we’re able to address both yard security and management because the data is the same data. For example, the check-in event and the security event are not two events; they are one event seen from two angles. The instant a truck reaches the gate, the system logging it for operations already holds nearly everything security needs, such as who is driving, what they are hauling, what the camera sees, and exactly when it happened. Recording that as an operations entry over here and a security entry over there was never a principle of good design.",[3289],{"type":149,"attrs":3290},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3292,"content":3293},{"textAlign":139},[3294],{"text":3295,"type":75,"marks":3296},"Security should live inside the system already running the gate.",[3297],{"type":149,"attrs":3298},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3300,"content":3301},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3302],{"text":3303,"type":75,"marks":3304},"Convergence",[3305],{"type":149,"attrs":3306},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3308,"content":3309},{"textAlign":139},[3310],{"text":3311,"type":75,"marks":3312},"Convergence matters because disconnected tools produce alerts, and unified systems produce decisions. A carrier-risk flag in one inbox, an ID scan in another, and a camera feed in a third are three pieces of information someone might later assemble into a conclusion, usually after the truck is already gone. That is retroactive security. It documents how the goods were lost.",[3313],{"type":149,"attrs":3314},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3316,"content":3317},{"textAlign":139},[3318],{"text":3319,"type":75,"marks":3320},"A fraudulent carrier at the gate is a decision that has to be made before the arm lifts. It can only be made if the carrier check, the driver's identity, the appointment, and the camera feed are all the same conversation, in the same place, at the same time. That is the entire point of bringing these capabilities together. Convergence isn't about owning fewer vendors, though you will. It's about turning a pile of after-the-fact records into a decision made at the only moment a decision still matters.",[3321],{"type":149,"attrs":3322},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3324,"content":3325},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3326],{"text":3327,"type":75,"marks":3328},"The yard has always been the supply chain’s soft spot",[3329],{"type":149,"attrs":3330},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3332,"content":3333},{"textAlign":139},[3334],{"text":3335,"type":75,"marks":3336},"To be clear, there’s always been freight fraud and the yard was always the soft spot. It’s because it’s where custody is most exposed. What's new is that the excuse is gone and the stakes are higher. Solutions exist that will allow, for the first time, the facility that released the load to prove who took it, prove they were authorized to, and prove that what was left matched what was supposed to. ",[3337],{"type":149,"attrs":3338},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3340,"content":3341},{"textAlign":139},[3342],{"text":3343,"type":75,"marks":3344},"That is what this moment in technology actually offers logistics. To give the yard the same visibility and accountability the rest of the supply chain has taken for granted for years.",[3345],{"type":149,"attrs":3346},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[2714],"Cargo fraud has made the yard the supply chain's most exposed point, yet yard security and yard management have always been treated as separate problems bought from separate vendors. Terminal's argument: AI-native development has collapsed that tradeoff, making it possible for the first time to converge both into one system at the gate, where custody actually changes and the decision to lift the arm still matters",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3351},{},"Why Yard Security Belongs Inside Your Yard Management System",{"id":3354,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":3355,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":3356,"is_external_url":49},188621303706158,"/storyblok/f/337048/800x533/789821de04/yard-gate.jpg",{},[],"Freight fraud made the yard the supply chain's soft spot. See why AI-native systems can finally converge yard security and management at the gate, where it counts.",{"value":2299,"plugin":2300},"if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-","all-resources/if-trust-in-freight-is-dead-why-is-it-still-running-the-yard-",-2310,[2305,3364,3365,3366,2733],"chain of custody","Logistics Technology ","security","3f685df9-91c4-4a64-9531-e80ac5078855","2026-06-17T23:36:58.081Z",[],{"name":3371,"created_at":3372,"published_at":3373,"updated_at":3374,"id":3375,"uuid":3376,"content":3377,"slug":4335,"full_slug":4336,"sort_by_date":139,"position":4337,"tag_list":4338,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":4342,"first_published_at":4343,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":4344,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"The Role of AI and Predictive Analytics in Next-Generation Yard Management Software","2025-11-09T08:37:42.265Z","2026-03-27T17:33:30.191Z","2026-03-27T17:33:30.221Z",110542283872435,"9477ad0f-88b0-47be-849f-3682c4ecfc3c",{"_uid":3378,"body":3379,"link":4322,"title":3371,"author":4323,"excerpt":4324,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2288,"seo_image":4325,"seo_title":4327,"button_text":132,"cover_image":4328,"gated_asset":4332,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":4333,"background_color":4334,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"4c66800a-ae4f-4406-a25d-7a120ba30c60",{"type":66,"content":3380},[3381,3389,3425,3433,3475,3484,3503,3517,3559,3577,3585,3594,3608,3616,3682,3707,3715,3723,3732,3741,3766,3774,3783,3797,3805,3871,3879,3888,3896,3905,3919,3951,3959,3968,3976,4026,4034,4042,4050,4059,4067,4081,4090,4098,4112,4121,4129,4171,4179,4188,4196,4205,4213,4222,4230,4239,4247,4256,4264,4273,4281,4300,4314],{"type":112,"attrs":3382,"content":3383},{"textAlign":139},[3384],{"text":3385,"type":75,"marks":3386},"Logistics yards have long been a problem area in the supply chain, suffering from manual processes, limited visibility, and reactive decision-making. You've probably experienced the frustration: trailers lost in large yards, gate congestion during busy times, and the ongoing challenge of coordinating asset movements efficiently. These issues directly lead to higher operational costs, delayed shipments, and reduced throughput.",[3387],{"type":149,"attrs":3388},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3390,"content":3391},{"textAlign":139},[3392,3398,3403,3409,3414,3420],{"text":3393,"type":75,"marks":3394},"AI in yard management",[3395,3397],{"type":149,"attrs":3396},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3399,"type":75,"marks":3400}," and ",[3401],{"type":149,"attrs":3402},{"color":1233},{"text":3404,"type":75,"marks":3405},"predictive analytics in logistics",[3406,3408],{"type":149,"attrs":3407},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3410,"type":75,"marks":3411}," are fundamentally changing this situation. ",[3412],{"type":149,"attrs":3413},{"color":1233},{"text":3415,"type":75,"marks":3416},"Next-generation yard management software",[3417,3419],{"type":149,"attrs":3418},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3421,"type":75,"marks":3422}," now uses computer vision, machine learning algorithms, and real-time data processing to turn yards from operational blind spots into precisely coordinated hubs. These technologies don't just digitize existing processes—they completely rethink how yards should operate.",[3423],{"type":149,"attrs":3424},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3426,"content":3427},{"textAlign":139},[3428],{"text":3429,"type":75,"marks":3430},"In this article, you'll discover:",[3431],{"type":149,"attrs":3432},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3434},[3435,3445,3455,3465],{"type":1347,"content":3436},[3437],{"type":112,"attrs":3438,"content":3439},{"textAlign":139},[3440],{"text":3441,"type":75,"marks":3442},"The specific problems that traditional yard operations face",[3443],{"type":149,"attrs":3444},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3446},[3447],{"type":112,"attrs":3448,"content":3449},{"textAlign":139},[3450],{"text":3451,"type":75,"marks":3452},"How AI-powered systems are transforming real-time asset tracking and gate automation",[3453],{"type":149,"attrs":3454},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3456},[3457],{"type":112,"attrs":3458,"content":3459},{"textAlign":139},[3460],{"text":3461,"type":75,"marks":3462},"The impact of predictive analytics in predicting congestion and optimizing resource allocation",[3463],{"type":149,"attrs":3464},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3466},[3467],{"type":112,"attrs":3468,"content":3469},{"textAlign":139},[3470],{"text":3471,"type":75,"marks":3472},"Concrete operational benefits you can expect from implementing these technologies",[3473],{"type":149,"attrs":3474},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3476,"content":3477},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3478],{"text":3479,"type":75,"marks":3480},"Understanding the Challenges in Traditional Yard Management",[3481,3483],{"type":149,"attrs":3482},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3485,"content":3486},{"textAlign":139},[3487,3492,3498],{"text":3488,"type":75,"marks":3489},"Logistics yards operating under traditional management systems face persistent ",[3490],{"type":149,"attrs":3491},{"color":1233},{"text":3493,"type":75,"marks":3494},"inefficiencies in logistics yards",[3495,3497],{"type":149,"attrs":3496},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3499,"type":75,"marks":3500}," that directly impact their bottom line. You've likely experienced the frustration of spending 20-30 minutes searching for a single trailer in a crowded yard—a scenario that plays out dozens of times daily across facilities still relying on outdated methods.",[3501],{"type":149,"attrs":3502},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3504,"content":3505},{"textAlign":139},[3506,3512],{"text":3507,"type":75,"marks":3508},"Manual yard operations",[3509,3511],{"type":149,"attrs":3510},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3513,"type":75,"marks":3514}," create a cascade of operational bottlenecks:",[3515],{"type":149,"attrs":3516},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3518},[3519,3529,3539,3549],{"type":1347,"content":3520},[3521],{"type":112,"attrs":3522,"content":3523},{"textAlign":139},[3524],{"text":3525,"type":75,"marks":3526},"Paper-based check-in processes that consume 15-20 minutes per transaction",[3527],{"type":149,"attrs":3528},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3530},[3531],{"type":112,"attrs":3532,"content":3533},{"textAlign":139},[3534],{"text":3535,"type":75,"marks":3536},"Physical yard walks requiring staff to manually record asset locations and conditions",[3537],{"type":149,"attrs":3538},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3540},[3541],{"type":112,"attrs":3542,"content":3543},{"textAlign":139},[3544],{"text":3545,"type":75,"marks":3546},"Phone calls and radio communications to coordinate moves between gate personnel, yard drivers, and dock supervisors",[3547],{"type":149,"attrs":3548},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3550},[3551],{"type":112,"attrs":3552,"content":3553},{"textAlign":139},[3554],{"text":3555,"type":75,"marks":3556},"Spreadsheet-based tracking systems that become outdated within minutes of updating",[3557],{"type":149,"attrs":3558},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3560,"content":3561},{"textAlign":139},[3562,3566,3572],{"text":1229,"type":75,"marks":3563},[3564],{"type":149,"attrs":3565},{"color":1233},{"text":3567,"type":75,"marks":3568},"trailer locating delays",[3569,3571],{"type":149,"attrs":3570},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3573,"type":75,"marks":3574}," inherent in these systems extend far beyond simple inconvenience. When your team can't quickly identify where specific trailers are parked, you're looking at increased driver detention fees—often $50-100 per hour—as carriers wait for their equipment. Missed appointment windows cascade into dock scheduling conflicts, forcing you to choose between paying premium freight rates or disappointing customers with delayed shipments.",[3575],{"type":149,"attrs":3576},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3578,"content":3579},{"textAlign":139},[3580],{"text":3581,"type":75,"marks":3582},"These challenges compound during peak periods. Limited real-time visibility means you're essentially managing your yard blind, reacting to problems rather than preventing them. The financial impact is substantial: facilities report throughput reductions of 30-40% compared to their theoretical capacity, with labor costs inflated by redundant manual verification tasks.",[3583],{"type":149,"attrs":3584},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3586,"content":3587},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3588],{"text":3589,"type":75,"marks":3590},"The Rise of AI-Native Yard Management Software Solutions",[3591,3593],{"type":149,"attrs":3592},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3595,"content":3596},{"textAlign":139},[3597,3603],{"text":3598,"type":75,"marks":3599},"AI-native YMS",[3600,3602],{"type":149,"attrs":3601},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3604,"type":75,"marks":3605}," represents a fundamental shift from traditional yard management systems that merely incorporate AI features as add-ons. These systems are built from the ground up with artificial intelligence embedded into their core architecture, enabling them to process vast amounts of data, learn from patterns, and make autonomous decisions in real-time.",[3606],{"type":149,"attrs":3607},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3609,"content":3610},{"textAlign":139},[3611],{"text":3612,"type":75,"marks":3613},"The defining characteristics of an AI-native yard management system include:",[3614],{"type":149,"attrs":3615},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3617},[3618,3634,3650,3666],{"type":1347,"content":3619},[3620],{"type":112,"attrs":3621,"content":3622},{"textAlign":139},[3623,3629],{"text":3624,"type":75,"marks":3625},"Computer vision capabilities ",[3626,3628],{"type":149,"attrs":3627},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3630,"type":75,"marks":3631},"that automatically identify and track assets without manual intervention",[3632],{"type":149,"attrs":3633},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3635},[3636],{"type":112,"attrs":3637,"content":3638},{"textAlign":139},[3639,3645],{"text":3640,"type":75,"marks":3641},"Self-learning algorithms ",[3642,3644],{"type":149,"attrs":3643},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3646,"type":75,"marks":3647},"that continuously improve operational workflows based on historical performance data",[3648],{"type":149,"attrs":3649},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3651},[3652],{"type":112,"attrs":3653,"content":3654},{"textAlign":139},[3655,3661],{"text":3656,"type":75,"marks":3657},"Real-time data processing infrastructure",[3658,3660],{"type":149,"attrs":3659},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3662,"type":75,"marks":3663}," that eliminates latency between physical yard activities and system updates",[3664],{"type":149,"attrs":3665},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3667},[3668],{"type":112,"attrs":3669,"content":3670},{"textAlign":139},[3671,3677],{"text":3672,"type":75,"marks":3673},"Modular architecture ",[3674,3676],{"type":149,"attrs":3675},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3678,"type":75,"marks":3679},"designed for rapid deployment and seamless scalability across multiple facilities",[3680],{"type":149,"attrs":3681},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3683,"content":3684},{"textAlign":139},[3685,3691,3696,3702],{"text":3686,"type":75,"marks":3687},"Terminal Industries' Yard Operating System™",[3688,3690],{"type":149,"attrs":3689},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3692,"type":75,"marks":3693}," exemplifies this new generation of ",[3694],{"type":149,"attrs":3695},{"color":1233},{"text":3697,"type":75,"marks":3698},"smart yard solutions",[3699,3701],{"type":149,"attrs":3700},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3703,"type":75,"marks":3704},". Terminal Industries' has positioned itself as a logistics tech innovator by developing an end-to-end yard execution platform that digitizes, automates, and optimizes yard logistics through its proprietary AI-native approach. Their system achieves 99.5% data accuracy through computer vision technology, a stark contrast to the error-prone manual data entry methods that plague traditional systems.",[3705],{"type":149,"attrs":3706},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3708,"content":3709},{"textAlign":139},[3710],{"text":3711,"type":75,"marks":3712},"What sets Terminal apart is their Terminal-in-a-Camera™ hardware kit, which can be deployed in hours without trenching or extensive infrastructure modifications. This plug-and-play approach addresses one of the most significant barriers to yard management system adoption: lengthy implementation timelines. Terminal's rapid deployment model delivers ROI in less than five months, making advanced yard technology accessible to mid-market operators who previously couldn't justify the investment in traditional yard management infrastructure.",[3713],{"type":149,"attrs":3714},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3716,"content":3717},{"textAlign":139},[3718],{"text":3719,"type":75,"marks":3720},"The AI-native architecture enables Terminal's system to orchestrate complex yard operations autonomously, from gate check-in through asset movement to final departure, without requiring constant manual oversight or static standard operating procedures.",[3721],{"type":149,"attrs":3722},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3724,"content":3725},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3726],{"text":3727,"type":75,"marks":3728},"Using Artificial Intelligence to Improve Yard Operations",[3729,3731],{"type":149,"attrs":3730},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":69,"attrs":3733,"content":3734},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[3735],{"text":3736,"type":75,"marks":3737},"How Computer Vision is Changing Logistics",[3738,3740],{"type":149,"attrs":3739},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3742,"content":3743},{"textAlign":139},[3744,3750,3755,3761],{"text":3745,"type":75,"marks":3746},"Computer vision in logistics ",[3747,3749],{"type":149,"attrs":3748},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3751,"type":75,"marks":3752},"has emerged as a game-changing technology that fundamentally transforms how you track and manage assets within your yard. This technology enables your yard management system to \"see\" and interpret visual data in real-time, delivering unprecedented accuracy levels. Terminal's proprietary computer vision capabilities achieve ",[3753],{"type":149,"attrs":3754},{"color":1233},{"text":3756,"type":75,"marks":3757},"50%+ improvement in data accuracy",[3758,3760],{"type":149,"attrs":3759},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3762,"type":75,"marks":3763},", eliminating the guesswork and errors that plague manual tracking methods.",[3764],{"type":149,"attrs":3765},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3767,"content":3768},{"textAlign":139},[3769],{"text":3770,"type":75,"marks":3771},"The technology works through strategically positioned cameras that continuously monitor your yard, automatically identifying and tracking every vehicle, trailer, and container as they move through different zones. You no longer need yard personnel walking around with clipboards or handheld scanners. The system captures license plates, container numbers, and asset identifiers instantly, updating your inventory in real-time without human intervention.",[3772],{"type":149,"attrs":3773},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3775,"content":3776},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[3777],{"text":3778,"type":75,"marks":3779},"How AI is Improving Gate Operations",[3780,3782],{"type":149,"attrs":3781},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3784,"content":3785},{"textAlign":139},[3786,3792],{"text":3787,"type":75,"marks":3788},"Automated gate processes using AI technology ",[3789,3791],{"type":149,"attrs":3790},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3793,"type":75,"marks":3794},"represent another critical application where artificial intelligence delivers immediate operational improvements. Gate operations have traditionally been bottlenecks in yard management, with manual check-in procedures consuming valuable time and creating frustration for drivers. Terminal's Gate Acceleration™ application demonstrates how AI can reduce gate transaction time by over 85% while simultaneously cutting errors by 75%.",[3795],{"type":149,"attrs":3796},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3798,"content":3799},{"textAlign":139},[3800],{"text":3801,"type":75,"marks":3802},"The automation happens through multiple AI-powered methods working in concert:",[3803],{"type":149,"attrs":3804},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3806},[3807,3823,3839,3855],{"type":1347,"content":3808},[3809],{"type":112,"attrs":3810,"content":3811},{"textAlign":139},[3812,3818],{"text":3813,"type":75,"marks":3814},"Optical Character Recognition (OCR) ",[3815,3817],{"type":149,"attrs":3816},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3819,"type":75,"marks":3820},"reads license plates, container numbers, and documentation automatically as vehicles approach the gate",[3821],{"type":149,"attrs":3822},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3824},[3825],{"type":112,"attrs":3826,"content":3827},{"textAlign":139},[3828,3834],{"text":3829,"type":75,"marks":3830},"Computer vision",[3831,3833],{"type":149,"attrs":3832},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3835,"type":75,"marks":3836}," verifies asset conditions, identifies damage, and confirms proper seals and security features",[3837],{"type":149,"attrs":3838},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3840},[3841],{"type":112,"attrs":3842,"content":3843},{"textAlign":139},[3844,3850],{"text":3845,"type":75,"marks":3846},"Intelligent access logic",[3847,3849],{"type":149,"attrs":3848},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3851,"type":75,"marks":3852}," validates credentials and determines appropriate routing based on pre-configured rules",[3853],{"type":149,"attrs":3854},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3856},[3857],{"type":112,"attrs":3858,"content":3859},{"textAlign":139},[3860,3866],{"text":3861,"type":75,"marks":3862},"Digital credentialing",[3863,3865],{"type":149,"attrs":3864},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3867,"type":75,"marks":3868}," replaces manual paperwork with automated verification systems",[3869],{"type":149,"attrs":3870},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3872,"content":3873},{"textAlign":139},[3874],{"text":3875,"type":75,"marks":3876},"You can configure these systems to handle different scenarios—from high-volume bobtail operations requiring fast-lane processing to high-security loads demanding additional verification steps.",[3877],{"type":149,"attrs":3878},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3880,"content":3881},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[3882],{"text":3883,"type":75,"marks":3884},"Using Predictive Analytics for Proactive Yard Management Strategies",[3885,3887],{"type":149,"attrs":3886},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3889,"content":3890},{"textAlign":139},[3891],{"text":3892,"type":75,"marks":3893},"Predictive analytics transforms yard management from a reactive scramble into a strategic operation. You can now anticipate bottlenecks before they happen, shifting from constantly putting out fires to making calculated plans.",[3894],{"type":149,"attrs":3895},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3897,"content":3898},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[3899],{"text":3900,"type":75,"marks":3901},"Congestion forecasting with predictive analytics ",[3902,3904],{"type":149,"attrs":3903},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3906,"content":3907},{"textAlign":139},[3908,3913,3914],{"text":3909,"type":75,"marks":3910},"Predictive analytics looks at historical data—seasonal changes, carrier schedules, and past throughput metrics—to figure out when your yard will be busiest. It also takes into account real-time data to predict congestion scenarios hours or even days in advance. This means you'll know exactly when that Friday afternoon rush will hit or when a specific carrier's schedule will cause a backup at the dock.",[3911],{"type":149,"attrs":3912},{"color":1233},{"type":618},{"text":3915,"type":75,"marks":3916},"With this knowledge, you can:",[3917],{"type":149,"attrs":3918},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3920},[3921,3931,3941],{"type":1347,"content":3922},[3923],{"type":112,"attrs":3924,"content":3925},{"textAlign":139},[3926],{"text":3927,"type":75,"marks":3928},"Adjust staffing levels",[3929],{"type":149,"attrs":3930},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3932},[3933],{"type":112,"attrs":3934,"content":3935},{"textAlign":139},[3936],{"text":3937,"type":75,"marks":3938},"Prepare extra resources",[3939],{"type":149,"attrs":3940},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3942},[3943],{"type":112,"attrs":3944,"content":3945},{"textAlign":139},[3946],{"text":3947,"type":75,"marks":3948},"Communicate proactively with carriers",[3949],{"type":149,"attrs":3950},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":3952,"content":3953},{"textAlign":139},[3954],{"text":3955,"type":75,"marks":3956},"Instead of finding out last minute that you need more yard drivers when the yard is already full, you can plan ahead and schedule them for the morning shift.",[3957],{"type":149,"attrs":3958},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":3960,"content":3961},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[3962],{"text":3963,"type":75,"marks":3964},"Resource optimization through data-driven insights",[3965,3967],{"type":149,"attrs":3966},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":3969,"content":3970},{"textAlign":139},[3971],{"text":3972,"type":75,"marks":3973},"Predictive models look at how long trailers stay in the yard, how often dock doors are used, and how trucks have moved in the past to make every part of yard operations better:",[3974],{"type":149,"attrs":3975},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":3977},[3978,3994,4010],{"type":1347,"content":3979},[3980],{"type":112,"attrs":3981,"content":3982},{"textAlign":139},[3983,3989],{"text":3984,"type":75,"marks":3985},"Dock scheduling intelligence",[3986,3988],{"type":149,"attrs":3987},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3990,"type":75,"marks":3991},": This takes into account how long it usually takes to load or unload based on who the carrier is, what type of product it is, and what time of day it is.",[3992],{"type":149,"attrs":3993},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":3995},[3996],{"type":112,"attrs":3997,"content":3998},{"textAlign":139},[3999,4005],{"text":4000,"type":75,"marks":4001},"Trailer placement optimization",[4002,4004],{"type":149,"attrs":4003},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4006,"type":75,"marks":4007},": This makes sure that trailers are parked in the best spots based on when they are expected to leave and which dock doors are available.",[4008],{"type":149,"attrs":4009},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4011},[4012],{"type":112,"attrs":4013,"content":4014},{"textAlign":139},[4015,4021],{"text":4016,"type":75,"marks":4017},"Dynamic space allocation",[4018,4020],{"type":149,"attrs":4019},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4022,"type":75,"marks":4023},": This changes how space is assigned in different areas of the yard as things change throughout the day.",[4024],{"type":149,"attrs":4025},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4027,"content":4028},{"textAlign":139},[4029],{"text":4030,"type":75,"marks":4031},"The algorithms learn from each transaction, continuously improving their predictions. For example, if a certain carrier always arrives 30 minutes late on Tuesdays, the system will take this into account when making scheduling recommendations. If certain types of products require longer loading times, dock assignments will be adjusted accordingly.",[4032],{"type":149,"attrs":4033},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4035,"content":4036},{"textAlign":139},[4037],{"text":4038,"type":75,"marks":4039},"You're no longer guessing which trailers should be parked near which doors or hoping you've set aside enough space in receiving areas. The data tells you exactly where resources should be placed and when they'll be needed.",[4040],{"type":149,"attrs":4041},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4043,"content":4044},{"textAlign":139},[4045],{"text":4046,"type":75,"marks":4047},"Incorporating elements from other fields such as predictive traffic management systems can further enhance these strategies by providing deeper insights into traffic patterns affecting yard operations. ",[4048],{"type":149,"attrs":4049},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4051,"content":4052},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4053],{"text":4054,"type":75,"marks":4055},"Ensuring Integration and Interoperability with Existing Systems for Seamless Operations",[4056,4058],{"type":149,"attrs":4057},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4060,"content":4061},{"textAlign":139},[4062],{"text":4063,"type":75,"marks":4064},"The true power of next-generation yard management software reveals itself through its ability to communicate with your existing technology infrastructure. You can't afford data silos when every minute of delay costs money and impacts customer satisfaction.",[4065],{"type":149,"attrs":4066},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4068,"content":4069},{"textAlign":139},[4070,4076],{"text":4071,"type":75,"marks":4072},"WMS integration challenges in yard management software",[4073,4075],{"type":149,"attrs":4074},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4077,"type":75,"marks":4078}," often stem from disparate data formats and communication protocols. Your warehouse management system tracks inventory, manages picking operations, and coordinates dock assignments. When your yard management solution operates in isolation, you're essentially running blind—unable to synchronize inbound trailer arrivals with warehouse receiving capacity or coordinate outbound shipments with dock availability.",[4079],{"type":149,"attrs":4080},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4082,"content":4083},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4084],{"text":4085,"type":75,"marks":4086},"How Terminal's Yard Operating System™ solves these integration complexities",[4087,4089],{"type":149,"attrs":4088},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4091,"content":4092},{"textAlign":139},[4093],{"text":4094,"type":75,"marks":4095},"Terminal's Yard Operating System™ addresses these integration complexities through its modern tech stack designed for seamless connectivity. The system automatically shares real-time asset location data with your WMS, enabling warehouse managers to prepare for incoming shipments before trailers reach the dock. This bidirectional data flow eliminates the manual handoffs that plague traditional yard operations.",[4096],{"type":149,"attrs":4097},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4099,"content":4100},{"textAlign":139},[4101,4107],{"text":4102,"type":75,"marks":4103},"TMS connectivity requirements for effective end-to-end execution",[4104,4106],{"type":149,"attrs":4105},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4108,"type":75,"marks":4109}," extend beyond simple data exchange. Your transportation management system needs accurate yard status information to provide realistic appointment windows and update carriers on detention times. When these systems communicate effectively, you create a continuous flow of information from the moment a carrier schedules a pickup through final departure.",[4110],{"type":149,"attrs":4111},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4113,"content":4114},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4115],{"text":4116,"type":75,"marks":4117},"Integration architecture must support the following:",[4118,4120],{"type":149,"attrs":4119},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4122,"content":4123},{"textAlign":139},[4124],{"text":4125,"type":75,"marks":4126},"The integration architecture must support:",[4127],{"type":149,"attrs":4128},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":4130},[4131,4141,4151,4161],{"type":1347,"content":4132},[4133],{"type":112,"attrs":4134,"content":4135},{"textAlign":139},[4136],{"text":4137,"type":75,"marks":4138},"Real-time asset visibility updates flowing to both WMS and TMS platforms",[4139],{"type":149,"attrs":4140},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4142},[4143],{"type":112,"attrs":4144,"content":4145},{"textAlign":139},[4146],{"text":4147,"type":75,"marks":4148},"Automated appointment synchronization between systems",[4149],{"type":149,"attrs":4150},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4152},[4153],{"type":112,"attrs":4154,"content":4155},{"textAlign":139},[4156],{"text":4157,"type":75,"marks":4158},"Exception alerts triggered across all connected platforms",[4159],{"type":149,"attrs":4160},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4162},[4163],{"type":112,"attrs":4164,"content":4165},{"textAlign":139},[4166],{"text":4167,"type":75,"marks":4168},"Unified reporting that consolidates data from yard, warehouse, and transportation operations",[4169],{"type":149,"attrs":4170},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4172,"content":4173},{"textAlign":139},[4174],{"text":4175,"type":75,"marks":4176},"You need API-first architecture that connects with your existing systems without requiring extensive custom development. The ability to deploy and integrate rapidly—as Terminal demonstrates with its deployment timeline—means you start realizing value without months of IT overhead.",[4177],{"type":149,"attrs":4178},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4180,"content":4181},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4182],{"text":4183,"type":75,"marks":4184},"Operational Benefits of AI and Predictive Analytics in Yard Management Software",[4185,4187],{"type":149,"attrs":4186},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4189,"content":4190},{"textAlign":139},[4191],{"text":4192,"type":75,"marks":4193},"Integrating AI and predictive analytics into yard management software brings significant improvements to various aspects of operations. These benefits will have a direct positive impact on your profits and day-to-day activities.",[4194],{"type":149,"attrs":4195},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4197,"content":4198},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4199],{"text":4200,"type":75,"marks":4201},"1. Faster Gate Processing with Automated Workflows",[4202,4204],{"type":149,"attrs":4203},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4206,"content":4207},{"textAlign":139},[4208],{"text":4209,"type":75,"marks":4210},"When you use AI-powered automation, gate processing times can be reduced by up to 85%. This is made possible through the use of computer vision technology, which eliminates the need for manual data entry, and intelligent workflows that guide assets through check-in procedures without requiring human involvement. For example, Terminal's Gate Acceleration™ application showcases this capability by processing vehicles in just seconds instead of minutes, enabling you to handle larger volumes without needing to hire additional staff.",[4211],{"type":149,"attrs":4212},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4214,"content":4215},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4216],{"text":4217,"type":75,"marks":4218},"2. Better Use of Space and Asset Optimization",[4219,4221],{"type":149,"attrs":4220},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4223,"content":4224},{"textAlign":139},[4225],{"text":4226,"type":75,"marks":4227},"Predictive analytics revolutionizes how you manage your yard space. By analyzing past patterns and current conditions, the system can recommend the best placement for trailers, resulting in a reduction of unnecessary moves by 50% or more. Additionally, it empowers you to foresee potential congestion before it happens and make real-time adjustments to your parking strategies based on anticipated incoming volumes.",[4228],{"type":149,"attrs":4229},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4231,"content":4232},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4233],{"text":4234,"type":75,"marks":4235},"3. Lower Labor Costs and Increased Productivity",[4236,4238],{"type":149,"attrs":4237},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4240,"content":4241},{"textAlign":139},[4242],{"text":4243,"type":75,"marks":4244},"With automated asset tracking, you can eliminate 90% of the time spent searching for assets manually, allowing your yard personnel to focus on more valuable tasks. The role of AI and predictive analytics in modern yard management software also includes intelligent task sequencing, which ensures that yard drivers receive optimized instructions for moving assets, minimizing empty travel distances and maximizing productive time.",[4245],{"type":149,"attrs":4246},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4248,"content":4249},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4250],{"text":4251,"type":75,"marks":4252},"4. Improved Relationships with Carriers and Reduced Detention Fees",[4253,4255],{"type":149,"attrs":4254},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4257,"content":4258},{"textAlign":139},[4259],{"text":4260,"type":75,"marks":4261},"By providing real-time visibility and using predictive dock scheduling techniques, you can reduce driver detention times by 12%. This means that you can give carriers accurate estimates of when they will arrive at your facility and process their vehicles more quickly, thereby strengthening partnerships while also reducing costs associated with delays and disputes.",[4262],{"type":149,"attrs":4263},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4265,"content":4266},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4267],{"text":4268,"type":75,"marks":4269},"Conclusion",[4270,4272],{"type":149,"attrs":4271},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4274,"content":4275},{"textAlign":139},[4276],{"text":4277,"type":75,"marks":4278},"AI and predictive analytics are transforming yard management, but this is just the start of a larger technological evolution in logistics operations. The groundwork is being laid for even more advanced capabilities that will redefine how yards operate.",[4279],{"type":149,"attrs":4280},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4282,"content":4283},{"textAlign":139},[4284,4289,4295],{"text":4285,"type":75,"marks":4286},"The integration of ",[4287],{"type":149,"attrs":4288},{"color":1233},{"text":4290,"type":75,"marks":4291},"autonomous vehicles",[4292,4294],{"type":149,"attrs":4293},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4296,"type":75,"marks":4297}," into yard operations promises to work seamlessly alongside AI-driven systems like Terminal's Yard Operating System™. These self-driving yard trucks can execute move tasks generated by predictive algorithms, creating a fully orchestrated environment where human operators focus on strategic decision-making rather than routine tasks.",[4298],{"type":149,"attrs":4299},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4301,"content":4302},{"textAlign":139},[4303,4309],{"text":4304,"type":75,"marks":4305},"IoT sensors",[4306,4308],{"type":149,"attrs":4307},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4310,"type":75,"marks":4311}," embedded throughout the yard will provide additional data streams that feed predictive models, enabling even more accurate forecasting of equipment needs, maintenance requirements, and operational bottlenecks. You'll see these sensors working in tandem with computer vision technology to create a comprehensive digital twin of your entire yard operation.",[4312],{"type":149,"attrs":4313},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4315,"content":4316},{"textAlign":139},[4317],{"text":4318,"type":75,"marks":4319},"The key to maximizing these efficiency gains lies in maintaining the right balance—leveraging automation where it excels while preserving human oversight for complex decision-making, exception handling, and strategic planning. This hybrid approach ensures you capture the speed and accuracy of AI while retaining the adaptability and judgment that human expertise provides.",[4320],{"type":149,"attrs":4321},{"color":1233},{"id":18,"url":18,"linktype":19,"fieldtype":20,"cached_url":18},[2267],"Logistics yards have long been a problem area in the supply chain, suffering from manual processes, limited visibility, and reactive decision-making. You've probably experienced the frustration: trailers lost in large yards, gate congestion during busy times, and the ongoing challenge of coordinating asset movements efficiently. These issues directly lead to higher operational costs, delayed shipments, and reduced throughput.\n",{"id":139,"alt":139,"name":18,"focus":139,"title":139,"source":139,"filename":18,"copyright":139,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":4326},{},"AI and Predictive Analytics in Next-Generation Yard Management Software",{"id":4329,"alt":18,"name":18,"focus":18,"title":18,"source":18,"filename":4330,"copyright":18,"fieldtype":1105,"meta_data":4331,"is_external_url":49},92143829909506,"/storyblok/f/337048/2146x1196/90c3d1e205/d.webp",{},[],"Explore how AI and predictive analytics are shaping next-generation yard management software—enabling smarter scheduling, real-time decision-making, and proactive supply chain execution.",{"value":2299,"plugin":2300},"the-role-of-ai-and-predictive-analytics-in-next-generation-yard-management-software","all-resources/the-role-of-ai-and-predictive-analytics-in-next-generation-yard-management-software",-1010,[2305,4339,4340,4341],"automation in operations","efficiency ","guide","cac1c0f2-212c-43de-b57f-eb5827022942","2025-11-18T15:02:42.866Z",[],{"name":4346,"created_at":4347,"published_at":4348,"updated_at":4349,"id":4350,"uuid":4351,"content":4352,"slug":5364,"full_slug":5365,"sort_by_date":139,"position":5366,"tag_list":5367,"is_startpage":49,"parent_id":2309,"meta_data":139,"group_id":5368,"first_published_at":5369,"release_id":139,"lang":1161,"path":139,"alternates":5370,"default_full_slug":139,"translated_slugs":139},"Comparing a Yard Management System vs. a Traditional Check-In Process: Which Saves More Time?","2025-11-09T08:43:29.698Z","2026-03-27T17:32:32.271Z","2026-03-27T17:32:32.294Z",110543706953910,"8da22268-4bd9-4742-a05f-34247577262b",{"_uid":4353,"body":4354,"link":5351,"title":4346,"author":5352,"excerpt":5353,"category":2287,"is_gated":49,"subtitle":18,"component":2288,"seo_image":5354,"seo_title":5356,"button_text":132,"cover_image":5357,"gated_asset":5361,"seo_noindex":49,"seo_description":5362,"background_color":5363,"featured_in_latest_news":49},"172c92b6-5e9a-4eb1-8bdc-ca1b476dd8a3",{"type":66,"content":4355},[4356,4364,4378,4397,4426,4435,4443,4452,4471,4585,4594,4602,4611,4619,4628,4694,4702,4710,4718,4727,4735,4749,4763,4771,4779,4811,4820,4839,4848,4872,4881,4910,4919,4927,4959,4968,4976,4985,4993,5002,5010,5019,5027,5036,5044,5052,5060,5069,5077,5085,5093,5138,5146,5155,5174,5188,5238,5257,5265,5284,5292,5327,5335,5343],{"type":112,"attrs":4357,"content":4358},{"textAlign":139},[4359],{"text":4360,"type":75,"marks":4361},"Yard operations serve as the critical connection point between transportation and warehouse activities in your supply chain. Every trailer that enters your facility, every dock door assignment, and every movement within your yard directly impacts your ability to ship and receive goods on time.",[4362],{"type":149,"attrs":4363},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4365,"content":4366},{"textAlign":139},[4367,4373],{"text":4368,"type":75,"marks":4369},"Efficient yard management isn't just a nice-to-have—it's essential for supply chain success.",[4370,4372],{"type":149,"attrs":4371},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4374,"type":75,"marks":4375}," When your yard runs smoothly, you reduce driver wait times, improve dock utilization, and maintain the flow of goods through your facility. When it doesn't, you face bottlenecks that ripple through your entire operation.",[4376],{"type":149,"attrs":4377},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4379,"content":4380},{"textAlign":139},[4381,4386,4392],{"text":4382,"type":75,"marks":4383},"The question facing many logistics operations today centers on methodology: should you stick with traditional manual check-in processes or invest in a ",[4384],{"type":149,"attrs":4385},{"color":1233},{"text":4387,"type":75,"marks":4388},"yard management system",[4389,4391],{"type":149,"attrs":4390},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4393,"type":75,"marks":4394},"? This comparison directly affects your bottom line through time savings, labor costs, and operational efficiency.",[4395],{"type":149,"attrs":4396},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4398,"content":4399},{"textAlign":139},[4400,4405,4411,4415,4421],{"text":4401,"type":75,"marks":4402},"This article examines both approaches to determine which method truly saves more time and delivers better results for your ",[4403],{"type":149,"attrs":4404},{"color":1233},{"text":4406,"type":75,"marks":4407},"logistics efficiency",[4408,4410],{"type":149,"attrs":4409},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":3399,"type":75,"marks":4412},[4413],{"type":149,"attrs":4414},{"color":1233},{"text":4416,"type":75,"marks":4417},"supply chain visibility",[4418,4420],{"type":149,"attrs":4419},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4422,"type":75,"marks":4423}," goals.",[4424],{"type":149,"attrs":4425},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4427,"content":4428},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4429],{"text":4430,"type":75,"marks":4431},"Understanding Traditional Check-In Processes in Yards",[4432,4434],{"type":149,"attrs":4433},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4436,"content":4437},{"textAlign":139},[4438],{"text":4439,"type":75,"marks":4440},"Traditional yard check-ins rely heavily on manual processes that create significant friction in daily operations. When a driver arrives at your facility, they typically need to present physical paperwork at the gate, wait for staff to verify documents, and communicate their purpose through phone calls or face-to-face interactions. Your gate personnel manually record trailer numbers, carrier information, and appointment details into spreadsheets or logbooks.",[4441],{"type":149,"attrs":4442},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4444,"content":4445},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4446],{"text":4447,"type":75,"marks":4448},"Pain Points of Manual Check-In",[4449,4451],{"type":149,"attrs":4450},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4453,"content":4454},{"textAlign":139},[4455,4460,4466],{"text":4456,"type":75,"marks":4457},"This ",[4458],{"type":149,"attrs":4459},{"color":1233},{"text":4461,"type":75,"marks":4462},"manual check-in",[4463,4465],{"type":149,"attrs":4464},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4467,"type":75,"marks":4468}," approach generates multiple pain points that compound throughout the day:",[4469],{"type":149,"attrs":4470},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":4472},[4473,4489,4516,4542,4558],{"type":1347,"content":4474},[4475],{"type":112,"attrs":4476,"content":4477},{"textAlign":139},[4478,4484],{"text":4479,"type":75,"marks":4480},"Extended Wait Times:",[4481,4483],{"type":149,"attrs":4482},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4485,"type":75,"marks":4486}," Drivers often experience extended wait times at gates during peak hours, sometimes idling for 30 minutes or more while your staff processes each vehicle sequentially.",[4487],{"type":149,"attrs":4488},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4490},[4491],{"type":112,"attrs":4492,"content":4493},{"textAlign":139},[4494,4500,4505,4511],{"text":4495,"type":75,"marks":4496},"Lost or Misread Information:",[4497,4499],{"type":149,"attrs":4498},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4501,"type":75,"marks":4502}," The reliance on ",[4503],{"type":149,"attrs":4504},{"color":1233},{"text":4506,"type":75,"marks":4507},"paperwork",[4508,4510],{"type":149,"attrs":4509},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4512,"type":75,"marks":4513}," means information gets lost, misread, or incorrectly transcribed—leading to trailers being directed to wrong dock doors or lost in the yard entirely.",[4514],{"type":149,"attrs":4515},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4517},[4518],{"type":112,"attrs":4519,"content":4520},{"textAlign":139},[4521,4527,4531,4537],{"text":4522,"type":75,"marks":4523},"Operational Blind Spots:",[4524,4526],{"type":149,"attrs":4525},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":103,"type":75,"marks":4528},[4529],{"type":149,"attrs":4530},{"color":1233},{"text":4532,"type":75,"marks":4533},"Communication delays",[4534,4536],{"type":149,"attrs":4535},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4538,"type":75,"marks":4539}," between drivers, gate staff, and warehouse teams create operational blind spots. Your yard personnel might spend hours making phone calls to locate specific trailers or confirm shipment details.",[4540],{"type":149,"attrs":4541},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4543},[4544],{"type":112,"attrs":4545,"content":4546},{"textAlign":139},[4547,4553],{"text":4548,"type":75,"marks":4549},"Disrupted Yard Flow:",[4550,4552],{"type":149,"attrs":4551},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4554,"type":75,"marks":4555}," When drivers can't reach the right person, they park wherever they find space, disrupting your planned yard flow.",[4556],{"type":149,"attrs":4557},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4559},[4560],{"type":112,"attrs":4561,"content":4562},{"textAlign":139},[4563,4569,4574,4580],{"text":4564,"type":75,"marks":4565},"Bottlenecks in High Volume Periods:",[4566,4568],{"type":149,"attrs":4567},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4570,"type":75,"marks":4571}," The impact on throughput becomes severe during high-volume periods. ",[4572],{"type":149,"attrs":4573},{"color":1233},{"text":4575,"type":75,"marks":4576},"Gate congestion",[4577,4579],{"type":149,"attrs":4578},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4581,"type":75,"marks":4582}," builds as each manual transaction takes 5-10 minutes, creating bottlenecks that ripple through your entire operation.",[4583],{"type":149,"attrs":4584},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4586,"content":4587},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4588],{"text":4589,"type":75,"marks":4590},"Lack of Visibility and Data Tracking",[4591,4593],{"type":149,"attrs":4592},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4595,"content":4596},{"textAlign":139},[4597],{"text":4598,"type":75,"marks":4599},"You lack real-time visibility into what assets occupy your yard, where they're located, or how long they've been sitting. This absence of data tracking prevents you from identifying patterns, measuring performance, or making informed decisions about yard optimization.",[4600],{"type":149,"attrs":4601},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4603,"content":4604},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4605],{"text":4606,"type":75,"marks":4607},"What is a Yard Management System (YMS)?",[4608,4610],{"type":149,"attrs":4609},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4612,"content":4613},{"textAlign":139},[4614],{"text":4615,"type":75,"marks":4616},"A Yard Management System (YMS) is a specialized software solution designed to digitize, automate, and optimize the complex operations that occur between the entrance and loading/unloading areas of a facility. Unlike traditional yards that rely on manual coordination methods, a YMS provides a centralized digital platform for managing all yard activities.",[4617],{"type":149,"attrs":4618},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4620,"content":4621},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4622],{"text":4623,"type":75,"marks":4624},"Key features of modern YMS platforms include:",[4625,4627],{"type":149,"attrs":4626},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1344,"content":4629},[4630,4646,4662,4678],{"type":1347,"content":4631},[4632],{"type":112,"attrs":4633,"content":4634},{"textAlign":139},[4635,4641],{"text":4636,"type":75,"marks":4637},"Automated gate check-ins:",[4638,4640],{"type":149,"attrs":4639},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4642,"type":75,"marks":4643}," These eliminate paperwork and reduce processing time from minutes to seconds.",[4644],{"type":149,"attrs":4645},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4647},[4648],{"type":112,"attrs":4649,"content":4650},{"textAlign":139},[4651,4657],{"text":4652,"type":75,"marks":4653},"Intelligent dock door allocation:",[4654,4656],{"type":149,"attrs":4655},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4658,"type":75,"marks":4659}," This feature matches trailers to optimal loading bays based on shipment priority, equipment type, and warehouse capacity.",[4660],{"type":149,"attrs":4661},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4663},[4664],{"type":112,"attrs":4665,"content":4666},{"textAlign":139},[4667,4673],{"text":4668,"type":75,"marks":4669},"Appointment scheduling systems:",[4670,4672],{"type":149,"attrs":4671},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4674,"type":75,"marks":4675}," These coordinate carrier arrivals and prevent congestion at the gate.",[4676],{"type":149,"attrs":4677},{"color":1233},{"type":1347,"content":4679},[4680],{"type":112,"attrs":4681,"content":4682},{"textAlign":139},[4683,4689],{"text":4684,"type":75,"marks":4685},"Real-time asset tracking:",[4686,4688],{"type":149,"attrs":4687},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4690,"type":75,"marks":4691}," This capability allows you to see the exact location of every trailer, container, or chassis in your yard at any given moment.",[4692],{"type":149,"attrs":4693},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4695,"content":4696},{"textAlign":139},[4697],{"text":4698,"type":75,"marks":4699},"The true power of a Yard Management System goes beyond its individual features. These platforms integrate smoothly with your existing warehouse management systems (WMS) and transportation management systems (TMS), creating a seamless flow of data throughout your entire supply chain. This integration addresses the critical visibility gap that exists between when a truck departs a carrier's network and when inventory enters your warehouse system.",[4700],{"type":149,"attrs":4701},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4703,"content":4704},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4705],{"text":4706,"type":75,"marks":4707},"Advanced solutions like Terminal Industries' AI-native Yard Operating System™ take automation in yards even further by using computer vision technology to achieve 99.5% accuracy in asset tracking. ",[4708],{"type":149,"attrs":4709},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4711,"content":4712},{"textAlign":139},[4713],{"text":4714,"type":75,"marks":4715},"This transforms how facilities manage the constant movement of equipment through their yards.",[4716],{"type":149,"attrs":4717},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4719,"content":4720},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4721],{"text":4722,"type":75,"marks":4723},"Time-Saving Advantages of a Yard Management System over Traditional Check-In Processes",[4724,4726],{"type":149,"attrs":4725},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4728,"content":4729},{"textAlign":139},[4730],{"text":4731,"type":75,"marks":4732},"The automation benefits of a modern YMS transform time-consuming manual tasks into streamlined digital workflows. When you eliminate the need for drivers to fill out paper forms, yard staff to manually log information, and dispatchers to coordinate movements through phone calls, you immediately reclaim hours of productive time each day. A digital gate process captures all necessary data automatically through computer vision and integrated systems, allowing trucks to move through check-in in minutes rather than the 15-30 minutes typical of manual processes.",[4733],{"type":149,"attrs":4734},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4736,"content":4737},{"textAlign":139},[4738,4744],{"text":4739,"type":75,"marks":4740},"Reduced wait times ",[4741,4743],{"type":149,"attrs":4742},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4745,"type":75,"marks":4746},"become immediately apparent at the gate. Traditional check-in processes create bottlenecks as drivers queue for manual verification, paperwork completion, and verbal instructions. Digital gate systems process vehicles continuously, with some advanced solutions like Terminal Industries' Gate Acceleration™ reducing gate transaction time by over 85%. You'll see truck congestion dissipate as automated workflows handle multiple simultaneous check-ins without requiring additional staff.",[4747],{"type":149,"attrs":4748},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4750,"content":4751},{"textAlign":139},[4752,4758],{"text":4753,"type":75,"marks":4754},"Optimized scheduling ",[4755,4757],{"type":149,"attrs":4756},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4759,"type":75,"marks":4760},"revolutionizes dock door operations. Instead of reactive dock assignments based on whoever arrives first, a YMS intelligently sequences loading and unloading activities based on priority, dock availability, and warehouse readiness. You gain faster loading/unloading cycles because the system ensures the right trailer arrives at the right dock at precisely the right time.",[4761],{"type":149,"attrs":4762},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4764,"content":4765},{"textAlign":139},[4766],{"text":4767,"type":75,"marks":4768},"Enhanced communication flow eliminates the errors and delays inherent in verbal instructions and manual coordination. Real-time updates reach all stakeholders simultaneously through the system, preventing miscommunication between drivers, yard personnel, and warehouse teams.",[4769],{"type":149,"attrs":4770},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":4772,"content":4773},{"textAlign":139},[4774],{"text":4775,"type":75,"marks":4776},"The quantitative impact speaks volumes: ",[4777],{"type":149,"attrs":4778},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":4780},[4781,4792],{"type":1347,"content":4782},[4783],{"type":112,"attrs":4784,"content":4785},{"textAlign":139},[4786],{"text":4787,"type":75,"marks":4788}," Workforce efficiency improvements of 25-30%",[4789,4791],{"type":149,"attrs":4790},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1347,"content":4793},[4794,4803],{"type":112,"attrs":4795,"content":4796},{"textAlign":139},[4797],{"text":4798,"type":75,"marks":4799},"Dock throughput increases of 20-40% ",[4800,4802],{"type":149,"attrs":4801},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4804,"content":4805},{"textAlign":139},[4806],{"text":4807,"type":75,"marks":4808},"represent measurable time savings that directly affect your bottom line.",[4809],{"type":149,"attrs":4810},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4812,"content":4813},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4814],{"text":4815,"type":75,"marks":4816},"Advanced Technologies Powering Modern YMS Solutions",[4817,4819],{"type":149,"attrs":4818},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4821,"content":4822},{"textAlign":139},[4823,4828,4834],{"text":4824,"type":75,"marks":4825},"The shift from traditional check-in processes to modern yard management isn't just about going digital—it's about using intelligent automation powered by breakthrough technologies. ",[4826],{"type":149,"attrs":4827},{"color":1233},{"text":4829,"type":75,"marks":4830},"AI-native Yard Operating System™",[4831,4833],{"type":149,"attrs":4832},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4835,"type":75,"marks":4836}," platforms represent the next generation of yard logistics, fundamentally different from legacy systems that simply digitized paper processes.",[4837],{"type":149,"attrs":4838},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4840,"content":4841},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4842],{"text":4843,"type":75,"marks":4844},"1. Computer Vision Technology: The Heart of Transformation",[4845,4847],{"type":149,"attrs":4846},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4849,"content":4850},{"textAlign":139},[4851,4857,4862,4867],{"text":4852,"type":75,"marks":4853},"Computer vision technology",[4854,4856],{"type":149,"attrs":4855},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4858,"type":75,"marks":4859}," is at the core of this change. Unlike traditional systems that require manual data entry or barcode scanning, modern solutions like Terminal's YOS use cameras equipped with AI to automatically identify and track every asset entering, moving through, and exiting your yard. This technology delivers ",[4860],{"type":149,"attrs":4861},{"color":1233},{"text":1600,"type":75,"marks":4863},[4864,4866],{"type":149,"attrs":4865},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4868,"type":75,"marks":4869}," for asset tracking, eliminating the human error that plagues manual processes. You no longer need yard jockeys to walk the lot with clipboards or rely on drivers to check in at kiosks.",[4870],{"type":149,"attrs":4871},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4873,"content":4874},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4875],{"text":4876,"type":75,"marks":4877},"2. Real-Time Data Infrastructure: Creating a Living Digital Twin",[4878,4880],{"type":149,"attrs":4879},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4882,"content":4883},{"textAlign":139},[4884,4888,4894,4899,4905],{"text":1229,"type":75,"marks":4885},[4886],{"type":149,"attrs":4887},{"color":1233},{"text":4889,"type":75,"marks":4890},"real-time data infrastructure",[4891,4893],{"type":149,"attrs":4892},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4895,"type":75,"marks":4896}," supporting these systems creates a living digital twin of your yard operations. Every trailer movement, every gate transaction, every dock assignment gets captured and processed instantly. This continuous data flow enables ",[4897],{"type":149,"attrs":4898},{"color":1233},{"text":4900,"type":75,"marks":4901},"SmartYard™ workflows",[4902,4904],{"type":149,"attrs":4903},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":4906,"type":75,"marks":4907}," that orchestrate complex yard activities without human intervention—from automated gate processes that recognize equipment and validate credentials to intelligent dock door assignments based on load characteristics and warehouse capacity.",[4908],{"type":149,"attrs":4909},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4911,"content":4912},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4913],{"text":4914,"type":75,"marks":4915},"3. Time Savings: Dramatic Reductions in Asset Search Times",[4916,4918],{"type":149,"attrs":4917},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4920,"content":4921},{"textAlign":139},[4922],{"text":4923,"type":75,"marks":4924},"The time savings are significant. Companies implementing these advanced systems report ",[4925],{"type":149,"attrs":4926},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":4928},[4929,4940],{"type":1347,"content":4930},[4931],{"type":112,"attrs":4932,"content":4933},{"textAlign":139},[4934],{"text":4935,"type":75,"marks":4936}," up to 90% reduction in asset search times—what used to take 20 minutes of driving around the yard now happens with a few clicks. ",[4937,4939],{"type":149,"attrs":4938},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1347,"content":4941},[4942,4951],{"type":112,"attrs":4943,"content":4944},{"textAlign":139},[4945],{"text":4946,"type":75,"marks":4947},"Driver detention fees drop by approximately 12% as automated scheduling and real-time visibility eliminate the confusion and delays that keep trucks waiting. ",[4948,4950],{"type":149,"attrs":4949},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4952,"content":4953},{"textAlign":139},[4954],{"text":4955,"type":75,"marks":4956},"The system knows where every asset is, where it needs to go, and orchestrates the movement without the constant radio chatter and phone calls that slow down traditional operations.",[4957],{"type":149,"attrs":4958},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4960,"content":4961},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[4962],{"text":4963,"type":75,"marks":4964},"Operational Efficiency Gains Beyond Time Savings with a Yard Management System",[4965,4967],{"type":149,"attrs":4966},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4969,"content":4970},{"textAlign":139},[4971],{"text":4972,"type":75,"marks":4973},"Time savings are just one part of the value a Yard Management System brings to your logistics operations. The impact of implementing a YMS goes beyond that, deeply influencing how you manage assets, control costs, and grow your business.",[4974],{"type":149,"attrs":4975},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4977,"content":4978},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4979],{"text":4980,"type":75,"marks":4981},"1. Improved Inventory Accuracy",[4982,4984],{"type":149,"attrs":4983},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":4986,"content":4987},{"textAlign":139},[4988],{"text":4989,"type":75,"marks":4990},"Inventory accuracy improves significantly when you switch from manual tracking methods to automated systems. Terminal's computer vision technology continuously monitors every asset in your yard, eliminating the discrepancies that often occur with traditional clipboard-and-spreadsheet approaches. You gain real-time visibility into what's actually on your property versus what your records claim, reducing the costly errors that happen when trailers go missing or get misplaced in large yard environments.",[4991],{"type":149,"attrs":4992},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":4994,"content":4995},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[4996],{"text":4997,"type":75,"marks":4998},"2. Reduced Detention Costs",[4999,5001],{"type":149,"attrs":5000},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5003,"content":5004},{"textAlign":139},[5005],{"text":5006,"type":75,"marks":5007},"Detention cost reduction becomes possible through precise scheduling and monitoring capabilities. When you know exactly where each trailer is located and can coordinate movements with great accuracy, drivers spend less time waiting. This helps you avoid expensive detention fees that accumulate when carriers sit idle at your facility. By improving appointment scheduling using automated dock door allocation, you're no longer paying penalties for inefficiencies that are out of sight and out of control.",[5008],{"type":149,"attrs":5009},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":5011,"content":5012},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[5013],{"text":5014,"type":75,"marks":5015},"3. Scalable Yard Operations",[5016,5018],{"type":149,"attrs":5017},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5020,"content":5021},{"textAlign":139},[5022],{"text":5023,"type":75,"marks":5024},"The scalability of yard operations takes on new meaning with cloud-based SaaS YMS platforms like Terminal's Yard Operating System™. You can expand across multiple facilities without making your operations more complicated. The unified view across your yard network means managing five warehouses doesn't require five times the effort. Seasonal peaks that once overwhelmed your manual processes become manageable events you can handle with your existing infrastructure.",[5025],{"type":149,"attrs":5026},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":5028,"content":5029},{"level":1283,"textAlign":139},[5030],{"text":5031,"type":75,"marks":5032},"4. Data-Driven Decision Making",[5033,5035],{"type":149,"attrs":5034},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5037,"content":5038},{"textAlign":139},[5039],{"text":5040,"type":75,"marks":5041},"Data-driven decision making replaces relying on instincts and guessing. Detailed performance metrics reveal patterns in your operations that you were previously unaware of, allowing you to optimize processes based on actual evidence instead of assumptions.",[5042],{"type":149,"attrs":5043},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5045,"content":5046},{"textAlign":139},[5047],{"text":5048,"type":75,"marks":5049},"Furthermore, the integration of a YMS with a robust warehouse management system can further enhance operational efficiency. These systems work together to streamline processes such as inventory management and order fulfillment, providing a seamless flow of information between the yard and warehouse.",[5050],{"type":149,"attrs":5051},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5053,"content":5054},{"textAlign":139},[5055],{"text":5056,"type":75,"marks":5057},"Lastly, for businesses in the food and beverage sector, implementing a YMS can be particularly beneficial. The unique challenges faced by this industry, such as strict compliance regulations and the need for precise inventory management, can be effectively addressed with a well-implemented Yard Management System.",[5058],{"type":149,"attrs":5059},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":5061,"content":5062},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[5063],{"text":5064,"type":75,"marks":5065},"Case Study Snapshot: The Impact of Implementing a Modern YMS on Time Savings and Efficiency Gains in Logistics Operations",[5066,5068],{"type":149,"attrs":5067},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5070,"content":5071},{"textAlign":139},[5072],{"text":5073,"type":75,"marks":5074},"The numbers tell a compelling story when you look at real-world deployments. Companies implementing Terminal's Yard Operating System™ have documented rapid ROI within just 5 months of deployment, demonstrating the immediate financial impact of transitioning from manual processes to automated yard operations.",[5075],{"type":149,"attrs":5076},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5078,"content":5079},{"textAlign":139},[5080],{"text":5081,"type":75,"marks":5082},"Organizations managing multiple warehouse facilities have reported throughput increased 50% after adopting modern YMS solutions. This dramatic improvement stems from the elimination of manual gate processing bottlenecks and the intelligent orchestration of yard movements. You gain comprehensive visibility across your entire warehouse network through a single-pane-of-glass interface, replacing the fragmented visibility that plagued traditional check-in methods.",[5083],{"type":149,"attrs":5084},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5086,"content":5087},{"textAlign":139},[5088],{"text":5089,"type":75,"marks":5090},"The transformation extends to asset tracking accuracy, where Terminal's computer vision technology delivers:",[5091],{"type":149,"attrs":5092},{"color":1233},{"type":1344,"content":5094},[5095,5106,5117],{"type":1347,"content":5096},[5097],{"type":112,"attrs":5098,"content":5099},{"textAlign":139},[5100],{"text":5101,"type":75,"marks":5102},"99.5% data accuracy—a stark contrast to the error-prone manual logging systems. ",[5103,5105],{"type":149,"attrs":5104},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1347,"content":5107},[5108],{"type":112,"attrs":5109,"content":5110},{"textAlign":139},[5111],{"text":5112,"type":75,"marks":5113},"Facilities have documented 85% reductions in gate processing times  ",[5114,5116],{"type":149,"attrs":5115},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":1347,"content":5118},[5119,5128,5130],{"type":112,"attrs":5120,"content":5121},{"textAlign":139},[5122],{"text":5123,"type":75,"marks":5124},"90% decreases in asset search times, translating directly into reduced driver detention fees and improved carrier relationships. ",[5125,5127],{"type":149,"attrs":5126},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5129},{"textAlign":139},{"type":112,"attrs":5131,"content":5132},{"textAlign":139},[5133],{"text":5134,"type":75,"marks":5135},"These measurable improvements validate the time-saving advantages of modern YMS platforms over conventional yard management approaches.",[5136],{"type":149,"attrs":5137},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5139,"content":5140},{"textAlign":139},[5141],{"text":5142,"type":75,"marks":5143},"Moreover, a significant part of this efficiency gain can be attributed to AI-driven data entry automation, which has revolutionized the way data is captured and processed in logistics operations.",[5144],{"type":149,"attrs":5145},{"color":1233},{"type":69,"attrs":5147,"content":5148},{"level":138,"textAlign":139},[5149],{"text":5150,"type":75,"marks":5151},"Challenges and Considerations When Transitioning from Traditional to Automated Yards with a Yard Management System Solution",[5152,5154],{"type":149,"attrs":5153},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"type":112,"attrs":5156,"content":5157},{"textAlign":139},[5158,5163,5169],{"text":5159,"type":75,"marks":5160},"Moving from manual check-in processes to an automated Yard Management System requires careful planning around several critical areas. You'll need to address ",[5161],{"type":149,"attrs":5162},{"color":1233},{"text":5164,"type":75,"marks":5165},"staff training needs",[5166,5168],{"type":149,"attrs":5167},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":5170,"type":75,"marks":5171}," as your team adapts to new digital workflows, and you may encounter resistance to change from employees comfortable with existing procedures. Change management in logistics technology adoption challenges often center on helping your workforce understand how automation enhances rather than replaces their roles.",[5172],{"type":149,"attrs":5173},{"color":1233},{"type":112,"attrs":5175,"content":5176},{"textAlign":139},[5177,5183],{"text":5178,"type":75,"marks":5179},"Technical integration",[5180,5182],{"type":149,"attrs":5181},{"color":1233},{"type":710},{"text":5184,"type":75,"marks":5185}," presents another significant consideration. Your new YMS must connect seamlessly with existing Warehouse Management Systems and Transportation Man